Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.62,English,,0,0,0,,Good morning. So today we continue the Vikings.\N{\rChinese}早安。今天我们继续学习维京人。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.10,0:00:07.90,English,,0,0,0,,And this morning we will look at their worldview,\N{\rChinese}今天早上我们来看看他们的世界观，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.24,0:00:09.58,English,,0,0,0,,their cultural system.\N{\rChinese}以及他们的文化体系。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.32,0:00:14.00,English,,0,0,0,,And as I mentioned last class,\N{\rChinese}如上节所说，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.10,0:00:15.66,English,,0,0,0,,I do believe that\N{\rChinese}我确实认为，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.66,0:00:21.16,English,,0,0,0,,the Viking culture is truly one of the outstanding cultures in Western civilization.\N{\rChinese}维京文化是西方文明中杰出的文化之一。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.72,0:00:23.44,English,,0,0,0,,The problem though\N{\rChinese}问题是我们对维京文化其实了解得很少。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.44,0:00:26.70,English,,0,0,0,,is we know actually very\N{\rChinese}我们对维京文化的了解其实很少。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.70,0:00:29.60,English,,0,0,0,,little about the Viking culture.\N{\rChinese}我们对维京文化的了解其实很少。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.00,0:00:31.46,English,,0,0,0,,And there are certain reasons for that.\N{\rChinese}还有一些原因可以解释这一点。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.19,0:00:34.18,English,,0,0,0,,The first reason is that\N{\rChinese}第一个原因是它们本来就是有目的的口头传统。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.18,0:00:37.44,English,,0,0,0,,they were purposefully an oral tradition.\N{\rChinese}they were purposefully an oral tradition.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.36,0:00:41.26,English,,0,0,0,,So it is our prejudice, it is our belief\N{\rChinese}于是我们就有了偏见，认为
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.26,0:00:42.64,English,,0,0,0,,that\N{\rChinese}是的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.64,0:00:47.36,English,,0,0,0,,a literary culture is superior to an oral tradition.\N{\rChinese}文学文化优于口头传统。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.56,0:00:49.20,English,,0,0,0,,It's harder to read and write.\N{\rChinese}读写更难一点。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.88,0:00:53.10,English,,0,0,0,,But what we forget is that when\N{\rChinese}但我们忘记的是，当我们从口头传统过渡到文字文化时，…
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.10,0:00:56.42,English,,0,0,0,,we transition from an oral tradition to a literary culture,\N{\rChinese}we transition from an oral tradition to a literary culture,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.66,0:00:58.72,English,,0,0,0,,we lose a lot in the process.\N{\rChinese}我们在这个过程中失去很多东西。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.00,0:01:02.34,English,,0,0,0,,And there are many cultures that\N{\rChinese}还有许多文化拥有读写的能力，却选择不去。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.34,0:01:06.00,English,,0,0,0,,have the capacity to read and write, but they chose not to.\N{\rChinese}have the capacity to read andwrite, but they chose not to.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.18,0:01:07.30,English,,0,0,0,,Because for them,\N{\rChinese}因为对他们来说，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.30,0:01:10.14,English,,0,0,0,,it was much more important to preserve their\N{\rChinese}口头传统比采用文字文化更重要。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.14,0:01:14.14,English,,0,0,0,,oral tradition than it was to adopt a literary culture.\N{\rChinese}他们更注重保存口头传统。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.98,0:01:17.46,English,,0,0,0,,And as I explained in today's lecture,\N{\rChinese}如我在今天的讲座中所说，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.78,0:01:22.66,English,,0,0,0,,there are many actually good reasons why you would want to preserve an oral tradition.\N{\rChinese}实际上有许多好理由让你想保存口头传统。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.00,0:01:24.28,English,,0,0,0,,That's the first reason.\N{\rChinese}这就是第一个理由。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.46,0:01:27.54,English,,0,0,0,,The Vikings were purposely an oral tradition culture.\N{\rChinese}维京人有意保持口头传统文化。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.96,0:01:29.94,English,,0,0,0,,The second reason is that...\N{\rChinese}第二个理由是……
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.00,0:01:34.44,English,,0,0,0,,Eventually the Vikings would convert to Christianity.\N{\rChinese}最终，维京人会皈依基督教。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.88,0:01:38.72,English,,0,0,0,,And in this conversion process, which would take generations,\N{\rChinese}在这段转换过程中，历经数代，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.22,0:01:44.04,English,,0,0,0,,they had to abandon a lot of their tradition\N{\rChinese}他们不得不放弃许多传统
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.04,0:01:45.26,English,,0,0,0,,and heritage.\N{\rChinese}与遗产。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.36,0:01:48.26,English,,0,0,0,,Including their mythologies\N{\rChinese}包括他们的神话
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.26,0:01:51.58,English,,0,0,0,,and their historical memory.\N{\rChinese}和他们的历史记忆。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.58,0:01:59.98,English,,0,0,0,,The Vikings were perceived as barbarians by the Christians.\N{\rChinese}维京人被基督徒视为蛮族。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.08,0:02:02.56,English,,0,0,0,,And because\N{\rChinese}并且因为
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.56,0:02:06.52,English,,0,0,0,,of the traumatic Viking encounters with Europe,\N{\rChinese}因与欧洲的创伤性维京相遇，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.70,0:02:09.02,English,,0,0,0,,there was an intention,\N{\rChinese}有意图，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.28,0:02:13.26,English,,0,0,0,,a purpose in trying to eradicate the Viking memory.\N{\rChinese}试图消除维京记忆的目的。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.14,0:02:19.26,English,,0,0,0,,So please keep in mind that\N{\rChinese}请记住，我们对维京人了解不多。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.26,0:02:21.18,English,,0,0,0,,we don't know that much about the Vikings.\N{\rChinese}我们对维京人了解不多。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.50,0:02:25.96,English,,0,0,0,,What we do know about the Vikings comes from two sources.\N{\rChinese}我们对维京人的了解来自两个来源。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.20,0:02:27.74,English,,0,0,0,,The first is archaeology.\N{\rChinese}第一个是考古学。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.90,0:02:29.62,English,,0,0,0,,We basically dug up their graves.\N{\rChinese}我们基本上挖掘了他们的坟墓。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.98,0:02:31.52,English,,0,0,0,,Some of their graves, not all of their graves.\N{\rChinese}我们挖掘了一部分坟墓，不是全部。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.78,0:02:34.00,English,,0,0,0,,And through their graves,\N{\rChinese}通过他们的坟墓，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.02,0:02:37.84,English,,0,0,0,,we're able to reconstruct some of their culture.\N{\rChinese}我们能够重建他们的一部分文化。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.66,0:02:47.56,English,,0,0,0,,But the main source of our understanding is through Norse mythology. Unfortunately,\N{\rChinese}但我们了解的主要来源是北欧神话。不幸的是，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.56,0:02:53.22,English,,0,0,0,,we only have a fraction of their entire mythology.\N{\rChinese}我们只拥有他们完整神话的一部分。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.66,0:02:55.16,English,,0,0,0,,Their mythology is vast,\N{\rChinese}他们的神话非常丰富。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.54,0:02:57.48,English,,0,0,0,,it's grand, it's epic, it's beautiful.\N{\rChinese}它宏伟、壮丽、优美。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.84,0:02:59.84,English,,0,0,0,,But we only have a fraction of that.\N{\rChinese}但我们只拥有其中的一部分。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.98,0:03:02.34,English,,0,0,0,,And unfortunately, over time,\N{\rChinese}而且不幸的是，随着时间的推移，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.74,0:03:05.86,English,,0,0,0,,Christians, Christian intellectuals,\N{\rChinese}基督徒，基督徒知识分子，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.86,0:03:08.96,English,,0,0,0,,want to sanctify\N{\rChinese}想要圣化
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.96,0:03:13.32,English,,0,0,0,,or purify the Norse mythology.\N{\rChinese}或净化北欧神话。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.68,0:03:16.72,English,,0,0,0,,Because the Norse mythology is extremely violent and sexual.\N{\rChinese}因为北欧神话极其暴力与性欲。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.98,0:03:18.50,English,,0,0,0,,And so they basically clean it up.\N{\rChinese}于是他们基本把它清理干净。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.86,0:03:20.08,English,,0,0,0,,Which means that\N{\rChinese}这意味着
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.08,0:03:24.82,English,,0,0,0,,a lot of what we have has been interpreted through Christian lens.\N{\rChinese}大量我们已有的内容已通过基督徒视角诠释。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.90,0:03:28.68,English,,0,0,0,,So please be careful about that, okay?\N{\rChinese}请注意这一点，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.98,0:03:33.66,English,,0,0,0,,I will try my best to reconstruct the Viking worldview.\N{\rChinese}我会尽力重建维京人的世界观。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.04,0:03:38.22,English,,0,0,0,,But please understand there are severe constraints and limitations.\N{\rChinese}请理解有很大限制与约束。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.92,0:03:43.30,English,,0,0,0,,And the way I will reconstruct the Viking worldview is by comparing\N{\rChinese}我重建维京世界观的方式是通过比较。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.30,0:03:47.42,English,,0,0,0,,and contrasting it with other mythologies, other civilizations, other cultures.\N{\rChinese}并与其他神话、文明、文化进行对照。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.38,0:03:52.28,English,,0,0,0,,And by using literary interpretation.\N{\rChinese}并通过文学诠释来实现。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.22,0:03:56.68,English,,0,0,0,,And ultimately by using my imagination,\N{\rChinese}最终通过我的想象来完成。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.04,0:03:59.16,English,,0,0,0,,okay? So please take what I say.\N{\rChinese}好的，请听我说。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.98,0:04:02.88,English,,0,0,0,,With a grain of salt. Be skeptical, be suspicious, ask questions,\N{\rChinese}加一点盐味。先怀疑，再怀疑，问问题，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.02,0:04:05.72,English,,0,0,0,,challenge me where you feel you need to, okay?\N{\rChinese}再来，我来挑战你，随你需要，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.88,0:04:08.58,English,,0,0,0,,Alright, so let's get started. Alright,\N{\rChinese}好了，开始吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.68,0:04:11.76,English,,0,0,0,,let's look at the Viking\N{\rChinese}让我们看看维京人的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.76,0:04:15.66,English,,0,0,0,,tradition in contrast to the Greeks\N{\rChinese}传统与希腊人和罗马人的对比，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.66,0:04:20.34,English,,0,0,0,,and the Romans, okay? So the Greeks, how did they see the world?\N{\rChinese}那么希腊人，他们是怎么看世界的？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.38,0:04:29.14,English,,0,0,0,,Remember, their idea of the community was the idea of the polis.\N{\rChinese}记住，他们对社区的想法就是城邦的概念。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.36,0:04:35.12,English,,0,0,0,,The polis gives us our word for politics.\N{\rChinese}城邦给了我们政治一词。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.38,0:04:38.28,English,,0,0,0,,And the idea is that the community is a group of men,\N{\rChinese}而这个概念是，社区是由一群人组成的。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.42,0:04:41.56,English,,0,0,0,,only men, who come together to debate and\N{\rChinese}只有人，聚在一起讨论并
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.56,0:04:43.98,English,,0,0,0,,argue for the future of the community.\N{\rChinese}为社区的未来辩论。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.56,0:04:48.72,English,,0,0,0,,And as such, the individual is someone\N{\rChinese}因而，个体即是一个人
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.72,0:04:50.84,English,,0,0,0,,who stands out, okay?\N{\rChinese}谁能脱颖而出，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.00,0:04:54.56,English,,0,0,0,,The word they use is eudaimonia or arete.\N{\rChinese}他们用的词是eudaimonia或arete。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.14,0:04:57.86,English,,0,0,0,,Eudaimonia means flourishing.\N{\rChinese}Eudaimonia就是繁荣。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.04,0:04:59.96,English,,0,0,0,,You can only flourish if you stand out.\N{\rChinese}只有在脱颖而出时才会繁荣。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.96,0:05:01.30,English,,0,0,0,,You stand out among a group of men.\N{\rChinese}你在一群人中脱颖而出。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.52,0:05:05.06,English,,0,0,0,,Arete is proving your excellence among a group of men.\N{\rChinese}arete证明你在一群人中的卓越。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.50,0:05:10.62,English,,0,0,0,,And so, I'll give you two examples of this Greek worldview.\N{\rChinese}于是，我给你举两个希腊世界观的例子。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.98,0:05:15.22,English,,0,0,0,,So the first is Achilles from the Iliad.\N{\rChinese}第一个是《伊利亚特》里的阿基琉斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.66,0:05:19.42,English,,0,0,0,,Remember, in the Iliad, Achilles tells everyone,\N{\rChinese}记住，在《伊利亚特》中，阿基琉斯对大家说…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.74,0:05:24.66,English,,0,0,0,,I am in Troy to seek personal glory.\N{\rChinese}我在特洛伊是为了个人荣耀。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.04,0:05:29.36,English,,0,0,0,,I don't care about the Greeks. I don't care about Helen or Troy.\N{\rChinese}我不在乎希腊人，也不在乎海伦或特洛伊。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.96,0:05:31.76,English,,0,0,0,,I don't care about what others think.\N{\rChinese}我不在乎别人怎么想。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.88,0:05:34.06,English,,0,0,0,,I just want to stand out.\N{\rChinese}我只想出众。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.20,0:05:36.58,English,,0,0,0,,I care about my own personal glory.\N{\rChinese}我在乎自己的个人荣耀。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.94,0:05:41.26,English,,0,0,0,,And that's why he's willing to let Hector\N{\rChinese}这就是他愿意让赫克托尔的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.26,0:05:44.50,English,,0,0,0,,and the Trojans almost destroy the Greek army.\N{\rChinese}并且特洛伊人几乎消灭了希腊军队。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.50,0:05:46.92,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so that's one example.\N{\rChinese}好的，这就是一个例子。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.06,0:05:51.78,English,,0,0,0,,Another example is from Herodotus, his book Historiis.\N{\rChinese}另一个例子来自赫罗多德的《历史》一书。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.86,0:05:56.36,English,,0,0,0,,It has to do with the Athenian leader Themisicles.\N{\rChinese}这与雅典领袖泰米西克斯有关。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.08,0:05:59.94,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so this is the year 480 B.C.\N{\rChinese}好的，这就是公元前480年。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.14,0:06:02.42,English,,0,0,0,,BC and\N{\rChinese}公元前480年。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.42,0:06:08.02,English,,0,0,0,,in the year 480 BCE the Persians are invading the Greek mainland.\N{\rChinese}公元前480年，波斯人入侵希腊本土。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.30,0:06:12.86,English,,0,0,0,,Sparta, Athens have united against the Persians.\N{\rChinese}斯巴达与雅典联手对抗波斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.90,0:06:16.82,English,,0,0,0,,The Persians burned down Athens and the Athenian people are on their ships.\N{\rChinese}波斯焚烧雅典，雅人乘船逃离。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.00,0:06:20.32,English,,0,0,0,,At this point the Spartans who\N{\rChinese}此时，掌握军权的斯巴达人
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.32,0:06:23.48,English,,0,0,0,,are in command of the military and\N{\rChinese}和雅典人展开激烈争论。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.48,0:06:25.14,English,,0,0,0,,the Athenians have a huge argument.\N{\rChinese}两方争执各自主张。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.40,0:06:27.36,English,,0,0,0,,The Athenians want to challenge\N{\rChinese}雅典人想在海上挑战波斯人
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.36,0:06:31.46,English,,0,0,0,,the Persians on the sea\N{\rChinese}并击败他们的海军。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.46,0:06:35.10,English,,0,0,0,,and defeat them and defeat their Navy.\N{\rChinese}并将其海军打败。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.76,0:06:39.68,English,,0,0,0,,The Spartans want to use their Navy to protect their homeland,\N{\rChinese}斯巴达人想用海军保卫本土，伯罗奔尼亚，抵御波斯入侵。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.02,0:06:42.56,English,,0,0,0,,the Peloponnese, against the Persian invasion\N{\rChinese}他们未能达成协议。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.56,0:06:45.92,English,,0,0,0,,and they cannot come to an agreement.\N{\rChinese}and they cannot come to an agreement.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.38,0:06:50.76,English,,0,0,0,,So what Themistocles does is he sends a spy,\N{\rChinese}于是色米斯托克勒斯所做的就是派遣间谍，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.94,0:06:53.92,English,,0,0,0,,a servant, to the king of the Persians and\N{\rChinese}一名仆人，送往波斯王那里并且
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.92,0:06:55.02,English,,0,0,0,,tell him, hey,\N{\rChinese}告诉他，嗨，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.02,0:07:00.76,English,,0,0,0,,the entire Greek Navy is stationed in Salamis.\N{\rChinese}整个希腊海军驻扎在萨拉米斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.90,0:07:06.26,English,,0,0,0,,But they're about to run away from you.\N{\rChinese}但他们正准备从你那里逃走。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.40,0:07:11.80,English,,0,0,0,,So here's a great chance to send your entire Persian Navy to crush the Greek Navy once\N{\rChinese}于是这是一次好机会，把整个波斯海军派去粉碎希腊海军。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.80,0:07:14.06,English,,0,0,0,,and for all. And that's what the king does.\N{\rChinese}并且如此，国王所作的就是这样。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.66,0:07:18.00,English,,0,0,0,,And at the Battle of Salamis the Athenians\N{\rChinese}在萨拉米斯之战，雅典人和斯巴达人...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.00,0:07:21.38,English,,0,0,0,,and the Spartans destroy the Persian Navy\N{\rChinese}雅典人和斯巴达人摧毁波斯海军
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.38,0:07:24.34,English,,0,0,0,,and turn the course of not only the war,\N{\rChinese}并改变战争的进程，并改变俄国历史的进程，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.50,0:07:28.14,English,,0,0,0,,but of Russian history because if the Persians hadn't won that day, then\N{\rChinese}因为如果波斯人那天没赢，我们就会生活在波斯影响的世界，而不是希腊影响的世界。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.14,0:07:34.04,English,,0,0,0,,we would be living in a Persian influenced world as opposed to a Greek influenced world.\N{\rChinese}我们将会在波斯影响的世界里生活，而不是希腊影响的世界。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.50,0:07:37.64,English,,0,0,0,,OK? But if you think about it, what Achilles and\N{\rChinese}好的？但如果你想想看，阿基琉斯和菲米克塞斯在做的事就是我们所说的起义、叛国或背叛。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.64,0:07:40.64,English,,0,0,0,,Phymexes are doing is what we\N{\rChinese}我们会把它们称作起义、叛国或背叛。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.64,0:07:44.48,English,,0,0,0,,would call sedition or treason or betrayal.\N{\rChinese}would call sedition or treason or betrayal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.76,0:07:47.04,English,,0,0,0,,OK? But that's just the Greek worldview.\N{\rChinese}好的？但那只是希腊的世界观。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.94,0:07:53.18,English,,0,0,0,,The Romans had a very different perspective.\N{\rChinese}罗马人有着截然不同的视角。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.18,0:07:57.74,English,,0,0,0,,They understood community as fundamentally about tradition.\N{\rChinese}他们把社区理解为根本在传统之中。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.98,0:08:01.22,English,,0,0,0,,And as such,\N{\rChinese}而且如此，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.24,0:08:03.90,English,,0,0,0,,the individual had to be\N{\rChinese}个体必须是
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.90,0:08:07.36,English,,0,0,0,,pious to the tradition,\N{\rChinese}对传统虔诚的
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.54,0:08:09.40,English,,0,0,0,,had to be loyal to the tradition.\N{\rChinese}个体必须忠于传统。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.76,0:08:11.22,English,,0,0,0,,They used the word piety.\N{\rChinese}他们用“虔诚”一词。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.98,0:08:16.36,English,,0,0,0,,Now, in China, we have a concept called filial piety.\N{\rChinese}现在，在中国，我们有一个叫做“孝顺”的概念。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.92,0:08:18.60,English,,0,0,0,,Guys, this is very important.\N{\rChinese}伙计们，这很重要。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.00,0:08:20.32,English,,0,0,0,,Completely opposite.\N{\rChinese}完全相反。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.32,0:08:22.02,English,,0,0,0,,In China,\N{\rChinese}在中国，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.18,0:08:26.10,English,,0,0,0,,filial piety means obedience to your father.\N{\rChinese}孝顺是对父亲的服从。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.42,0:08:28.56,English,,0,0,0,,What your father says is right.\N{\rChinese}父亲说的就是对的。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.68,0:08:32.90,English,,0,0,0,,That's what it means. But in Rome,\N{\rChinese}这就是它的意思。但在罗马，
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.12,0:08:38.12,English,,0,0,0,,piety means loyalty to the traditions of Rome.\N{\rChinese}孝顺是对罗马传统的忠诚。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.44,0:08:40.94,English,,0,0,0,,So the classic example is Julius Caesar.\N{\rChinese}经典例子是朱利叶斯·凯撒。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.57,0:08:44.00,English,,0,0,0,,Julius Caesar wanted to be king.\N{\rChinese}朱利叶斯·凯撒想成为国王。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.12,0:08:46.50,English,,0,0,0,,He was about to break a lot of Roman traditions.\N{\rChinese}他即将打破许多罗马传统。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.96,0:08:49.12,English,,0,0,0,,So his friends, including...\N{\rChinese}于是他的朋友们，包括……
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.12,0:08:53.68,English,,0,0,0,,... His biological son, Marcus Brutus, killed him.\N{\rChinese}他的亲生儿子马鲁斯·布鲁图斯将他杀死。
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.78,0:09:00.04,English,,0,0,0,,It was more important for Marcus Brutus to be loyal to the traditions of Rome than to\N{\rChinese}马鲁斯·布鲁图斯更重要的是对罗马传统的忠诚，而不是对父亲的忠诚。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.28,0:09:03.28,English,,0,0,0,,be loyal to his father.\N{\rChinese}于是这就是罗马传统。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.22,0:09:05.94,English,,0,0,0,,So that's the Roman tradition.\N{\rChinese}So that's the Roman tradition.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.10,0:09:08.94,English,,0,0,0,,Then you have the Viking tradition.\N{\rChinese}然后你会得到维京传统。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.74,0:09:13.44,English,,0,0,0,,For the Vikings, and this is very interesting,\N{\rChinese}对于维京人来说，这一点非常有趣，
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.64,0:09:16.18,English,,0,0,0,,the community is a set of stories.\N{\rChinese}社区就是一组故事。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.50,0:09:22.10,English,,0,0,0,,And stories are not the same as tradition.\N{\rChinese}故事并非传统相同。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.82,0:09:26.92,English,,0,0,0,,Tradition is what is past.\N{\rChinese}传统是过去的事物。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.68,0:09:29.36,English,,0,0,0,,It is what is written down.\N{\rChinese}它是被记录下来的东西。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.30,0:09:33.18,English,,0,0,0,,Stories are memories that are living.\N{\rChinese}故事是活生生的记忆。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.70,0:09:36.24,English,,0,0,0,,That which a community tells about itself.\N{\rChinese}那是社区对自己的叙述。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.62,0:09:40.98,English,,0,0,0,,And therefore, there is a flexibility to these stories.\N{\rChinese}因此，故事具有灵活性。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.34,0:09:44.20,English,,0,0,0,,They can be reimagined over and over.\N{\rChinese}它们可以一遍又一遍地重新想象。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.40,0:09:46.16,English,,0,0,0,,The basic structure... the outline is the same.\N{\rChinese}基本结构……大纲相同。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.16,0:09:50.94,English,,0,0,0,,But the community has to constantly relive\N{\rChinese}但社区必须不断再体验。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.94,0:09:52.34,English,,0,0,0,,and reimagine these stories.\N{\rChinese}并重新想象这些故事。
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.72,0:09:57.56,English,,0,0,0,,And therefore, the individual is a person\N{\rChinese}因此，个体就是一个人
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.56,0:10:01.88,English,,0,0,0,,who acts out these stories.\N{\rChinese}并把这些故事演绎出来
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.32,0:10:03.26,English,,0,0,0,,And\N{\rChinese}并
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.26,0:10:08.78,English,,0,0,0,,he acts out these stories either through ritual,\N{\rChinese}他通过仪式把这些故事演绎出来，
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.04,0:10:12.42,English,,0,0,0,,either through adventure, or exploration.\N{\rChinese}通过冒险或探索来实现。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.98,0:10:16.14,English,,0,0,0,,So this is a hard idea to understand.\N{\rChinese}这就是一个难以理解的概念。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.14,0:10:19.40,English,,0,0,0,,How is this different from the Roman tradition?\N{\rChinese}这与罗马传统有什么不同？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.80,0:10:25.28,English,,0,0,0,,But let me tell you a story to illustrate this Viking culture.\N{\rChinese}让我给你讲个故事来说明这种维京文化。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.12,0:10:28.92,English,,0,0,0,,So 30 years ago, a long time ago,\N{\rChinese}于是三十年前，久远的过去，我正与新朋友共进午餐。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.14,0:10:32.12,English,,0,0,0,,I was having lunch with a new friend.\N{\rChinese}我正与新朋友共进午餐。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.42,0:10:35.28,English,,0,0,0,,And he went to a very good school called Georgetown.\N{\rChinese}他就读了一所很好的学校，叫乔治城大学。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.62,0:10:37.08,English,,0,0,0,,It's based in Washington, D.C.\N{\rChinese}它位于华盛顿特区。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.46,0:10:39.04,English,,0,0,0,,And it's where Bill Clinton went.\N{\rChinese}它就是比尔·克林顿去的地方。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.18,0:10:44.76,English,,0,0,0,,This is where a lot of the Washington foreign policy elite go to school.\N{\rChinese}这里是许多华盛顿外交政策精英去读书的地方。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.64,0:10:49.08,English,,0,0,0,,And he went to a very good school called Georgetown. And he told me that at Georgetown,\N{\rChinese}他就读了一所很好的学校，叫乔治城大学。他告诉我，乔治城大学有一个传统，学生之间的竞赛。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.44,0:10:53.88,English,,0,0,0,,there's a tradition, a competition among undergraduates.\N{\rChinese}有一个传统，学生之间的竞赛。
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.22,0:10:56.38,English,,0,0,0,,And the competition is who\N{\rChinese}竞赛是……
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.38,0:11:01.08,English,,0,0,0,,can go the furthest to do the most useless thing.\N{\rChinese}可以走得最远去做最无用的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.08,0:11:04.72,English,,0,0,0,,And a lot of undergraduates participate in this competition.\N{\rChinese}许多本科生都参加这场竞赛。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.16,0:11:09.40,English,,0,0,0,,So what my friend and his friend did was one day they got in a car.\N{\rChinese}于是我和我的朋友那天上车去了。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.50,0:11:12.72,English,,0,0,0,,They drove 12 hours to Canada, the Canadian border.\N{\rChinese}他们开车12小时到达加拿大边境。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.88,0:11:14.18,English,,0,0,0,,They crossed the Canadian border.\N{\rChinese}他们越过加拿大边境。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.44,0:11:15.92,English,,0,0,0,,Then they got out of the car.\N{\rChinese}随后他们下车。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.14,0:11:19.00,English,,0,0,0,,And went into the forest to take a piss.\N{\rChinese}然后他们进入森林去撒尿。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.72,0:11:23.12,English,,0,0,0,,Then they got back in the car and drove all the way back to Georgetown.\N{\rChinese}随后他们又上车，开车一路回到乔治城。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.38,0:11:26.60,English,,0,0,0,,They spent 24 hours driving so\N{\rChinese}他们花了24小时开车回去。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.60,0:11:29.94,English,,0,0,0,,that they could take a piss in Canada.\N{\rChinese}他们能在加拿大撒尿。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.64,0:11:35.04,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Now you think this sounds really stupid.\N{\rChinese}好吧？现在你觉得这听起来很傻。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.28,0:11:39.62,English,,0,0,0,,But the most interesting thing about the story is that it is memorable.\N{\rChinese}但这件事最有趣的地方在于它很容易记住。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.54,0:11:41.78,English,,0,0,0,,Right? Memorable.\N{\rChinese}对吧？记住了。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.98,0:11:45.14,English,,0,0,0,,And what this means is that...\N{\rChinese}这意味着……
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.14,0:11:48.68,English,,0,0,0,,50 years after they graduate from Georgetown,\N{\rChinese}五十年后他们从乔治城毕业。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.02,0:11:52.10,English,,0,0,0,,people will still remember what they did.\N{\rChinese}人们仍会记得他们所做的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.44,0:11:56.56,English,,0,0,0,,Not only that, but they'll tell their friends, they'll tell their colleagues, they'll tell their children.\N{\rChinese}不只是如此，他们还会告诉朋友、同事、孩子。
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.74,0:11:59.72,English,,0,0,0,,So this memory will persist over time.\N{\rChinese}于是这记忆会随时间延续。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.80,0:12:06.52,English,,0,0,0,,No one should remember who got the best grades at Georgetown that year.\N{\rChinese}没有人会记得那年乔治城的最佳成绩是谁的。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.12,0:12:09.50,English,,0,0,0,,No one should remember who had the most money, who\N{\rChinese}没有人会记得谁拥有最多的钱，谁在一生中赚得最多。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.50,0:12:13.52,English,,0,0,0,,made the most money in his or her life.\N{\rChinese}没有人会记得谁拥有最多的钱，谁在一生中赚得最多。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.68,0:12:16.64,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But everyone should remember these two guys who\N{\rChinese}好的？但大家都要记住这两个人，他们……
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.64,0:12:19.12,English,,0,0,0,,got in their car and drove 24 hours just so that\N{\rChinese}他们上车开了24小时，只是为了……
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.12,0:12:21.46,English,,0,0,0,,they can go to Canada to take a piss.\N{\rChinese}他们可以去加拿大去撒个尿。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.22,0:12:24.16,English,,0,0,0,,Alright? So that is Viking culture.\N{\rChinese}好了？所以这就是维京文化。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.38,0:12:29.34,English,,0,0,0,,It's not about winning glory or protecting tradition.\N{\rChinese}这不是关于赢得荣耀或守护传统。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.52,0:12:32.10,English,,0,0,0,,It's about doing what is shocking,\N{\rChinese}这关乎做出令人震惊的事。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.34,0:12:36.96,English,,0,0,0,,what is new, what will add to the imagination\N{\rChinese}什么新鲜事，什么会增添想象
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.96,0:12:39.08,English,,0,0,0,,and the memory of the community.\N{\rChinese}以及社区的记忆
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.42,0:12:42.98,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Does that make sense? Alright.\N{\rChinese}好的？那有道理吗？好了。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.98,0:12:48.60,English,,0,0,0,,So their main memory is of course their mythology.\N{\rChinese}所以他们的主要记忆当然是他们的神话。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.94,0:12:52.18,English,,0,0,0,,Norse mythology. And Norse mythology, I would argue,\N{\rChinese}北欧神话。再说北欧神话，我想说，
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.42,0:12:55.88,English,,0,0,0,,is the greatest mythology\N{\rChinese}是最伟大的神话。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.88,0:12:58.42,English,,0,0,0,,in human history.\N{\rChinese}在人的历史中。
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.56,0:13:00.32,English,,0,0,0,,We still have it today.\N{\rChinese}我们今天仍然拥有它。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.82,0:13:03.70,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? You might have seen these Marvel movies, right?\N{\rChinese}好吧？你可能看过这些漫威电影，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.02,0:13:06.26,English,,0,0,0,,Thor, the Thor series.\N{\rChinese}Thor，雷神系列。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.84,0:13:10.56,English,,0,0,0,,There are a lot of TV shows based on the Vikings.\N{\rChinese}有许多以维京为题材的电视剧。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.88,0:13:12.96,English,,0,0,0,,So the Viking culture, the Norse mythology, is based on the Vikings.\N{\rChinese}因此，维京文化与北欧神话都源自维京人。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.96,0:13:14.48,English,,0,0,0,,It's still celebrated today.\N{\rChinese}它至今仍被庆祝。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.94,0:13:18.40,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So let me explain to you why I would argue\N{\rChinese}好吧？让我来解释一下，我之所以这么说的原因是。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.40,0:13:22.40,English,,0,0,0,,that Norse mythology is probably the\N{\rChinese}北欧神话大概是。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.40,0:13:25.52,English,,0,0,0,,greatest cosmological system we have.\N{\rChinese}我们拥有的最宏大的宇宙系统。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.02,0:13:29.18,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So first it's grand.\N{\rChinese}好的。首先它很宏大。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.66,0:13:33.36,English,,0,0,0,,In this mythology there are nine realms.\N{\rChinese}在这神话里有九个世界。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.58,0:13:36.84,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? One, two, three, four,\N{\rChinese}好吧？一、二、三、四，
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.04,0:13:39.42,English,,0,0,0,,five, six, seven, eight, nine.\N{\rChinese}五、六、七、八、九。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.72,0:13:42.66,English,,0,0,0,,And it's all connected by a world tree.\N{\rChinese}并且它们都通过一棵世界树相连。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.66,0:13:44.46,English,,0,0,0,,Called Idrisel. Okay?\N{\rChinese}称为伊德里塞尔。好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.56,0:13:46.54,English,,0,0,0,,No one knows what this world tree looks like.\N{\rChinese}没有人知道这棵世界树长什么样。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.66,0:13:50.36,English,,0,0,0,,But it's basically the equivalent of God in this system.\N{\rChinese}但它基本相当于这个体系里的上帝。
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.90,0:13:52.42,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And in this,\N{\rChinese}好吧？在这个里，
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.60,0:13:56.40,English,,0,0,0,,in Idrisel there are three gods\N{\rChinese}在伊德里塞尔有三位神
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.40,0:14:01.06,English,,0,0,0,,who control the fate and destiny of the world called the Nons.\N{\rChinese}他们掌控着被称为Nons的世界的命运与宿命
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.20,0:14:03.16,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So it's very grand and epic.\N{\rChinese}好吧？所以它非常宏大而史诗。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.54,0:14:08.06,English,,0,0,0,,Also, what's important to understand is there's nothing outside this universe.\N{\rChinese}另外，重要的是要明白，宇宙之外没有任何东西。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.40,0:14:09.98,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? This is it.\N{\rChinese}好吧？这就是了。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.54,0:14:13.78,English,,0,0,0,,Second. The second is that it's complete.\N{\rChinese}第二点。第二点是它完整。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.22,0:14:19.90,English,,0,0,0,,What I mean by that is it has a beginning and it has an end.\N{\rChinese}我所说的意思是它有开始也有结束。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.34,0:14:23.20,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The beginning is there's a rift\N{\rChinese}好的？开始就是有裂缝。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.20,0:14:28.32,English,,0,0,0,,and from the rift steps a frost giant named Imar.\N{\rChinese}并且从裂缝中出现了一个名叫伊玛尔的霜巨人。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.96,0:14:31.96,English,,0,0,0,,And then comes a cow, a cosmic cow,\N{\rChinese}随后出现了一头宇宙之牛，宇宙之牛。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.16,0:14:34.92,English,,0,0,0,,who then licks the ice and that\N{\rChinese}它随后舔舌冰面，随后舔舌冰面。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.92,0:14:37.46,English,,0,0,0,,releases another god who\N{\rChinese}释放另一位神祇，随后会诞生另一位神祇。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.46,0:14:40.34,English,,0,0,0,,will eventually give birth to another god.\N{\rChinese}随后诞生另一位神祇。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.34,0:14:43.32,English,,0,0,0,,Who will give birth to the three major gods including Odin.\N{\rChinese}随后诞生三位主神，其中包括奥丁。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.48,0:14:46.52,English,,0,0,0,,And these three major gods will kill Imar and\N{\rChinese}这些三位主神将杀死伊玛尔并
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.52,0:14:49.68,English,,0,0,0,,from Imar's carcass they will build the universe.\N{\rChinese}从伊玛尔尸体中建造宇宙
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.00,0:14:51.86,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? That's the beginning.\N{\rChinese}好了？这就是开始。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.12,0:14:54.86,English,,0,0,0,,But there's also an end. And the end is what I call,\N{\rChinese}但也有一个结局。那就是我所说的，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.04,0:14:57.00,English,,0,0,0,,what's what they call Ragnarok.\N{\rChinese}那就是他们所说的，拉格纳罗克。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.96,0:15:03.64,English,,0,0,0,,Ragnarok. And Ragnarok is the end of everything.\N{\rChinese}拉格纳罗克。拉格纳罗克就是一切的终结。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.96,0:15:06.76,English,,0,0,0,,It is a final battle between the gods.\N{\rChinese}它是一场神祇之间的终极之战。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.92,0:15:08.20,English,,0,0,0,,What we'll call the Ishir.\N{\rChinese}我们称之为伊希尔。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.28,0:15:13.12,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So Odin is the all father,\N{\rChinese}好了？于是奥丁是全父。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.24,0:15:15.74,English,,0,0,0,,the main god. But in all children are called the Ishir.\N{\rChinese}主神。又有一群被称作伊希尔的孩子。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.82,0:15:21.58,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The Ishir will fight a final cosmic battle between them\N{\rChinese}好了？伊希尔将与他们与敌人展开终极宇宙之战。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.58,0:15:23.06,English,,0,0,0,,and their enemies. And\N{\rChinese}and their enemies. And
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.06,0:15:27.02,English,,0,0,0,,in this final battle everything will die.\N{\rChinese}在这场终极之战中，一切都将消亡。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.78,0:15:29.96,English,,0,0,0,,Nothing will be left. Okay?\N{\rChinese}什么也不剩。好了？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.56,0:15:33.82,English,,0,0,0,,Then that's it. Now,\N{\rChinese}就这样。现在，
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.82,0:15:38.46,English,,0,0,0,,as I mentioned, the Christian tradition will take the story.\N{\rChinese}正如我所说，基督教传统会接手这个故事。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.46,0:15:40.86,English,,0,0,0,,And adapt it for its own ends.\N{\rChinese}然后再按自己的需要改编。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.10,0:15:43.92,English,,0,0,0,,So in the Christian tradition Ragnarok does happen.\N{\rChinese}于是，在基督教传统里，拉格纳罗克确实发生了。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.08,0:15:49.04,English,,0,0,0,,But guess what? After the end of the world two humans,\N{\rChinese}但你猜怎么了？世界结束后，两个凡人，一男一女，将从废墟中出现。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.36,0:15:52.04,English,,0,0,0,,a man and a woman, will emerge from the destruction.\N{\rChinese}他们将重新构造世界。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.36,0:15:54.22,English,,0,0,0,,And reconstitute the world.\N{\rChinese}And reconstitutethe world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.34,0:15:56.48,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? That's the Christian tradition.\N{\rChinese}好的？这就是基督教传统。
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.64,0:15:59.26,English,,0,0,0,,In the Norse tradition everything ends.\N{\rChinese}在北欧传统里，一切都以此结束。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.38,0:16:04.46,English,,0,0,0,,And you may think to yourself, oh, well this sounds extremely pessimistic.\N{\rChinese}你可能会想，哦，这听起来很悲观。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.22,0:16:08.30,English,,0,0,0,,But that's only because we're looking at it from our perspective.\N{\rChinese}但那只是因为我们从自己的视角来看。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.30,0:16:11.96,English,,0,0,0,,From the perspective of the Vikings the end of the world means\N{\rChinese}从维京人的视角看，世界的终结意味着……
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.96,0:16:16.16,English,,0,0,0,,that you must cherish every single day.\N{\rChinese}于是你必须珍惜每一天。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.42,0:16:18.10,English,,0,0,0,,Live with honor.\N{\rChinese}与荣耀同行。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.34,0:16:20.96,English,,0,0,0,,Live with glory. Live with courage.\N{\rChinese}与光荣同行，勇敢同行。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.24,0:16:26.70,English,,0,0,0,,Cherish every moment.\N{\rChinese}珍惜每一刻。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.18,0:16:29.94,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And that's the idea.\N{\rChinese}好的？这就是意思。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.06,0:16:34.22,English,,0,0,0,,The third thing about Norse mythology is that it's unified.\N{\rChinese}关于北欧神话的第三点是它是统一的。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.54,0:16:37.62,English,,0,0,0,,So all the characters.\N{\rChinese}所以所有角色都在同一体系内。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.62,0:16:38.90,English,,0,0,0,,Everything that\N{\rChinese}一切发生的事都包含在这神话之中。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.90,0:16:42.68,English,,0,0,0,,happens is contained within this mythology.\N{\rChinese}并为这神话的发展作出了贡献。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.00,0:16:46.18,English,,0,0,0,,And contributes to development of this mythology.\N{\rChinese}And contributes to development of this mythology.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.58,0:16:49.22,English,,0,0,0,,So this mythology not only includes gods.\N{\rChinese}所以这神话不仅包含神祇。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.54,0:16:50.80,English,,0,0,0,,But also includes humans.\N{\rChinese}而且也包含人类。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.08,0:16:53.68,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Who\N{\rChinese}好的吗？谁？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.68,0:16:56.50,English,,0,0,0,,are champions of the gods.\N{\rChinese}是神的冠军。
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.96,0:17:00.68,English,,0,0,0,,So there's a very famous love story within this mythology.\N{\rChinese}于是这神话中有一段非常著名的爱情故事。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.72,0:17:05.02,English,,0,0,0,,Between a human named Sigard.\N{\rChinese}一位名叫西加德的人类之间。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.12,0:17:08.00,English,,0,0,0,,And a Valkyrie.\N{\rChinese}并且有一位女武士。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.20,0:17:10.90,English,,0,0,0,,Who is a servant of the gods.\N{\rChinese}她是神的仆人。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.18,0:17:14.12,English,,0,0,0,,Named Brumhilde.\N{\rChinese}名为布鲁姆希德。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.50,0:17:19.00,English,,0,0,0,,Eventually what will happen is that\N{\rChinese}最终会发生的事是……
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.00,0:17:21.72,English,,0,0,0,,there will be a very famous German composer named Wagner.\N{\rChinese}会出现一位非常著名的德国作曲家——瓦格纳。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.00,0:17:26.50,English,,0,0,0,,Who will take the story of Sigard, Brumhilde and this entire Norse mythology.\N{\rChinese}他将把西加德、布鲁姆希德以及整个北欧神话搬上舞台。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.80,0:17:30.10,English,,0,0,0,,And construct something called the Ring Cycle.\N{\rChinese}并构造出名为环形周期的作品。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.02,0:17:35.00,English,,0,0,0,,Which is the most famous opera in German history.\N{\rChinese}它是德国历史上最著名的歌剧。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.00,0:17:39.84,English,,0,0,0,,And this becomes one of the foundations of modern German culture.\N{\rChinese}这成为现代德国文化的基石之一。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.42,0:17:43.08,English,,0,0,0,,This Norse mythology will also become\N{\rChinese}这段北欧神话也将成为托尔金史诗《指环王》的灵感。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.08,0:17:48.50,English,,0,0,0,,the inspiration for Tolkien's epic called Lord of the Rings.\N{\rChinese}好的？所以。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.76,0:17:54.26,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So\N{\rChinese}Okay? So
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.26,0:17:55.46,English,,0,0,0,,these are the two most obvious\N{\rChinese}这些是北欧神话至今仍影响我们世界的两个最明显例子。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.46,0:17:58.62,English,,0,0,0,,examples of how Norse\N{\rChinese}这些是北欧神话至今仍影响我们世界的两个最明显例子。
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.62,0:18:01.98,English,,0,0,0,,mythology still impacts our world today.\N{\rChinese}这些是北欧神话至今仍影响我们世界的两个最明显例子。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.18,0:18:04.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And as we go along the semester.\N{\rChinese}好的？接下来学期继续。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.38,0:18:06.12,English,,0,0,0,,I will show other influences.\N{\rChinese}我会展示其他影响。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.02,0:18:09.56,English,,0,0,0,,Alright? So\N{\rChinese}好的？那就开始吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.56,0:18:12.74,English,,0,0,0,,what Norse mythology is trying\N{\rChinese}北欧神话所要表达的是什么
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.74,0:18:17.44,English,,0,0,0,,to do is create community among the Vikings.\N{\rChinese}做的事是让维京人形成社区。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.64,0:18:19.74,English,,0,0,0,,And instill certain values.\N{\rChinese}并灌输某些价值观。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.22,0:18:23.20,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The three major values that\N{\rChinese}好的？这三大价值观是……
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.20,0:18:26.56,English,,0,0,0,,these stories manifest and express are.\N{\rChinese}这些故事所体现并表达的三大价值观是……
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.08,0:18:31.98,English,,0,0,0,,Courage. The courage to explore.\N{\rChinese}勇气。探索的勇气。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.26,0:18:34.30,English,,0,0,0,,The courage to seek what is new.\N{\rChinese}寻找新事物的勇气。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.38,0:18:37.94,English,,0,0,0,,And unknown. To venture forth into the unknown.\N{\rChinese}并且未知。踏入未知之旅。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.22,0:18:42.04,English,,0,0,0,,Because Vikings are mainly explorers and adventurers.\N{\rChinese}因为维京人主要是探险者与冒险家。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.50,0:18:48.72,English,,0,0,0,,Raiding is only a small part of their community.\N{\rChinese}掠夺只是他们社群的一小部分。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.98,0:18:52.00,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Second is the idea of loyalty.\N{\rChinese}好？第二个是忠诚的概念。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.56,0:18:56.50,English,,0,0,0,,And this is a very important concept.\N{\rChinese}而这是一项非常重要的概念。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.90,0:18:59.12,English,,0,0,0,,When you go out on new adventures.\N{\rChinese}当你踏上新的冒险之旅时。
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.44,0:19:01.64,English,,0,0,0,,You usually go out with your brothers.\N{\rChinese}你通常会和兄弟们一起出发。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.84,0:19:03.48,English,,0,0,0,,Your friends. Okay?\N{\rChinese}你的朋友们。好？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.48,0:19:06.48,English,,0,0,0,,It's like a band of brothers. So you have to survive.\N{\rChinese}像一支兄弟团体。你得先存活。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.76,0:19:09.68,English,,0,0,0,,You have to be willing to die for them.\N{\rChinese}你得愿意为他们赴死。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.88,0:19:11.18,English,,0,0,0,,You have to die for each other.\N{\rChinese}你得为彼此赴死。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.86,0:19:15.64,English,,0,0,0,,If the survival of the group requires you to make the ultimate sacrifice.\N{\rChinese}如果集体生存需要你作出终极牺牲。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.22,0:19:17.98,English,,0,0,0,,You have to do so. Okay?\N{\rChinese}你得这么做。好？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.98,0:19:20.84,English,,0,0,0,,Loyalty. Loyalty means love for each other.\N{\rChinese}忠诚。忠诚即彼此相爱。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.12,0:19:22.58,English,,0,0,0,,It does not mean obedience.\N{\rChinese}它并不意味着服从。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.26,0:19:25.40,English,,0,0,0,,Remember in the Viking world it is very egalitarian.\N{\rChinese}记住，在维京世界里很平等。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.00,0:19:27.20,English,,0,0,0,,There's very little hierarchy.\N{\rChinese}层级很少。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.78,0:19:29.06,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? There are high status people.\N{\rChinese}好的？有高阶层的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.52,0:19:32.48,English,,0,0,0,,But they are high status because they are proving themselves worthier.\N{\rChinese}但他们之所以高阶，是因为他们证明自己更值得。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.48,0:19:34.16,English,,0,0,0,,Than the others.\N{\rChinese}比其他人更值得。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.34,0:19:36.62,English,,0,0,0,,Because they are braver. Because they are stronger.\N{\rChinese}因为他们更勇敢。因为他们更强壮。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.84,0:19:38.76,English,,0,0,0,,Because they are more clever. Okay?\N{\rChinese}因为他们更聪明。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.20,0:19:42.68,English,,0,0,0,,The last Viking value is resourcefulness.\N{\rChinese}最后一个维京价值是机智。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.40,0:19:49.04,English,,0,0,0,,So the idea here is.\N{\rChinese}所以这里的意思是。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.54,0:19:51.90,English,,0,0,0,,When you venture off into the unknown.\N{\rChinese}当你踏入未知之时。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.64,0:19:55.16,English,,0,0,0,,You cannot know what to expect.\N{\rChinese}你无法预料会遇到什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.36,0:19:57.72,English,,0,0,0,,You can't plan ahead. You can't be strategic.\N{\rChinese}你不能提前计划。你不能做战略。
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.18,0:20:01.40,English,,0,0,0,,So you can only be resourceful.\N{\rChinese}于是你只能机智。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.40,0:20:05.72,English,,0,0,0,,Meaning you must respond to the danger as it arises.\N{\rChinese}意思是你必须在危险出现时立即应对。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.24,0:20:09.06,English,,0,0,0,,You have to be very, what we call, quick -witted.\N{\rChinese}你必须非常机灵——我们称之为快活。”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.44,0:20:12.24,English,,0,0,0,,You have to have street smarts.\N{\rChinese}你得有街头智慧。”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.26,0:20:16.40,English,,0,0,0,,So these are the three main values or ideas\N{\rChinese}于是这三点即是主要价值或观念。”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.40,0:20:19.44,English,,0,0,0,,that Norse mythology is trying to express\N{\rChinese}那北欧神话正试图表达的事物
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.44,0:20:22.22,English,,0,0,0,,and instill in the people.\N{\rChinese}并在人民中灌注之意
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.08,0:20:26.42,English,,0,0,0,,So that's a general introduction to Viking culture.\N{\rChinese}于是这便是维京文化的概括性介绍
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.42,0:20:29.94,English,,0,0,0,,Now what I will do is I will provide evidence\N{\rChinese}现在我将提供证据
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.94,0:20:33.10,English,,0,0,0,,and examples for this argument.\N{\rChinese}以及例子来支撑这个论点
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.46,0:20:35.16,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Alright.\N{\rChinese}好的？好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.68,0:20:39.56,English,,0,0,0,,But, is this clear to you guys?\N{\rChinese}但这对你们来说清楚吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.36,0:20:43.34,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Alright, so now let's do the PPT.\N{\rChinese}好的。好了，现在我们来做PPT。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.38,0:20:51.92,English,,0,0,0,,And look at the evidence\N{\rChinese}再看一下证据。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.92,0:20:53.44,English,,0,0,0,,and the examples.\N{\rChinese}以及例子。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.12,0:20:56.72,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Okay. Alright.\N{\rChinese}好的。好的。好了。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.84,0:20:58.18,English,,0,0,0,,The Viking worldview.\N{\rChinese}维京人的世界观。
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.16,0:21:02.22,English,,0,0,0,,Alright. First thing I need you guys to understand is\N{\rChinese}好的。首先我想让你们明白的是
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.22,0:21:05.38,English,,0,0,0,,that every culture, every society,\N{\rChinese}每个文化、每个社会，
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.50,0:21:09.54,English,,0,0,0,,fundamentally asks itself three questions.\N{\rChinese}本质上都会问自己三个问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.46,0:21:13.68,English,,0,0,0,,That this painting from Paul Gauguin captures.\N{\rChinese}那幅由保罗·高更绘制的画作所捕捉的画面。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.92,0:21:15.50,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Where do we come from?\N{\rChinese}好的？我们从哪里来？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.66,0:21:17.66,English,,0,0,0,,What are we? Where are we going?\N{\rChinese}我们是什么？我们要去哪里？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.80,0:21:20.80,English,,0,0,0,,Every culture is trying to grapple with these three questions.\N{\rChinese}每个文化都在努力回答这三个问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.04,0:21:23.44,English,,0,0,0,,Paul Gauguin, I'm not sure if you know who he is.\N{\rChinese}保罗·高更，我不确定你是否知道他是谁。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.56,0:21:25.24,English,,0,0,0,,He is a very famous French artist.\N{\rChinese}他是一位非常著名的法国艺术家。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.24,0:21:28.12,English,,0,0,0,,He started off actually as a financier, a stockbroker.\N{\rChinese}他最初是个金融家，股票经纪人。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.34,0:21:33.60,English,,0,0,0,,And then he basically became disgusted with the material lifestyle of modern society.\N{\rChinese}随后他对现代社会的物质生活方式基本感到厌倦。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.90,0:21:37.64,English,,0,0,0,,So he got on a boat and went to Tahiti where he painted.\N{\rChinese}于是他登船前往塔希提，去那里作画。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.92,0:21:40.44,English,,0,0,0,,He interacted with the natives.\N{\rChinese}他与当地人互动。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.84,0:21:45.10,English,,0,0,0,,And through this interaction, he began to grapple with what it means to be a human.\N{\rChinese}通过这种互动，他开始思考人类的意义。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.24,0:21:46.44,English,,0,0,0,,What is the human project?\N{\rChinese}人类的项目是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.80,0:21:48.02,English,,0,0,0,,And what he believes and\N{\rChinese}他所相信的以及他认为大多数人类学家所相信的是要问这三个问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.02,0:21:51.32,English,,0,0,0,,what most actually anthropologists believe is to be\N{\rChinese}他所相信的以及他认为大多数人类学家所相信的是要问这三个问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.32,0:21:54.04,English,,0,0,0,,human is to ask these three questions.\N{\rChinese}他所相信的以及他认为大多数人类学家所相信的是要问这三个问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.46,0:21:56.66,English,,0,0,0,,Where do we come from?\N{\rChinese}我们从哪里来？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.76,0:21:58.80,English,,0,0,0,,Why are we here? Where are we going?\N{\rChinese}我们为什么在这里？我们要去哪里？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.06,0:22:03.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And that's ultimately what Norse mythology is trying to grapple with as well.\N{\rChinese}好的？这正是北欧神话试图探讨的核心。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.36,0:22:10.18,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So again, we know our evidence,\N{\rChinese}好的。再说一次，我们的证据是……
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.26,0:22:12.64,English,,0,0,0,,our understanding of the Vikings comes from archaeology.\N{\rChinese}我们对维京人的了解来自考古学。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.14,0:22:14.98,English,,0,0,0,,So we are able to dig up their graves.\N{\rChinese}于是我们就能挖掘他们的坟墓。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.10,0:22:18.06,English,,0,0,0,,And what we discover is, and it's very interesting,\N{\rChinese}而我们发现的事，且非常有趣，
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.12,0:22:21.84,English,,0,0,0,,is that each grave is unique.\N{\rChinese}每个坟墓都是独一的。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.24,0:22:25.88,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And it seems that\N{\rChinese}好？看起来是这样。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.88,0:22:29.56,English,,0,0,0,,each grave in its own way is telling a story about\N{\rChinese}每个坟墓以自己的方式讲述着这人的故事。
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.56,0:22:30.72,English,,0,0,0,,who this person is.\N{\rChinese}这坟墓的样子就是……
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.47,0:22:33.80,English,,0,0,0,,It's like this grave was not meant\N{\rChinese}It's like this grave was not meant
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.80,0:22:38.78,English,,0,0,0,,just to send this individual into the afterworld,\N{\rChinese}仅仅是把这人送入来世
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.90,0:22:42.52,English,,0,0,0,,but also to remember him or her\N{\rChinese}也为了记住他或她
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.52,0:22:45.74,English,,0,0,0,,and his or her achievements in life.\N{\rChinese}以及他或她生前的成就
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.00,0:22:47.08,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So\N{\rChinese}好的？那么
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.08,0:22:51.50,English,,0,0,0,,let's look at some\N{\rChinese}让我们看看
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.50,0:22:53.58,English,,0,0,0,,reconstruction of these graves.\N{\rChinese}这些坟墓的重建
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.62,0:22:54.84,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And as you can see,\N{\rChinese}好的？正如你所见，
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.02,0:22:58.70,English,,0,0,0,,this woman is buried with tools,\N{\rChinese}这位女子与工具一起葬于此，
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.12,0:23:03.30,English,,0,0,0,,an arrow, as well as a dead horse.\N{\rChinese}一支箭以及一匹已死的马也随葬。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.16,0:23:06.74,English,,0,0,0,,So we're not able to reconstruct her story,\N{\rChinese}于是我们无法重建她的故事，
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.04,0:23:09.58,English,,0,0,0,,but obviously those who\N{\rChinese}但显然那些认识她的人确切知道故事所代表的意义。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.58,0:23:13.62,English,,0,0,0,,knew her knew exactly what the story represented.\N{\rChinese}knew her knew exactly what the story represented.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.88,0:23:18.50,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? This is another example\N{\rChinese}好的？这又是一个例子
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.50,0:23:20.76,English,,0,0,0,,where a man is buried with his ship.\N{\rChinese}在这里，一个人被葬在他的船里
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.76,0:23:26.04,English,,0,0,0,,The Vikings are the only society to bury people in ships.\N{\rChinese}维京人是唯一把人葬在船里的社会
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.56,0:23:29.78,English,,0,0,0,,Another example.\N{\rChinese}另一个例子。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.98,0:23:31.78,English,,0,0,0,,And as you can see, they're all unique.\N{\rChinese}正如你所见，它们各不相同。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.96,0:23:35.96,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, what's really interesting for us is to appreciate\N{\rChinese}事实上，对我们来说真正有趣的，是欣赏……
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.96,0:23:41.34,English,,0,0,0,,that funerals were the most important aspect of Viking society.\N{\rChinese}那时葬礼是维京社会最重要的方面。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.80,0:23:43.74,English,,0,0,0,,It's what brought the community together.\N{\rChinese}它把社区团结在一起。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.28,0:23:46.46,English,,0,0,0,,And it was what they remembered the most.\N{\rChinese}而它们最记得的就是这一点。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.68,0:23:50.36,English,,0,0,0,,It is funerals are what contributed to historical memory.\N{\rChinese}葬礼是构成历史记忆的关键。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.36,0:23:52.52,English,,0,0,0,,And as you can see,\N{\rChinese}正如你所见，
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.68,0:23:54.96,English,,0,0,0,,this funeral is extremely elaborate,\N{\rChinese}这场葬礼极为繁复。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.28,0:23:57.74,English,,0,0,0,,involving a lot of animal sacrifice.\N{\rChinese}涉及大量动物祭祀。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.96,0:24:00.30,English,,0,0,0,,These horses are being gathered up to be sacrificed.\N{\rChinese}这些马被聚集起来进行祭祀。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.76,0:24:02.10,English,,0,0,0,,There's also human sacrifice.\N{\rChinese}还有人祭。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.74,0:24:06.66,English,,0,0,0,,And these funerals can last for a long time, 10 days.\N{\rChinese}并且这些葬礼可持续十天之久。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.16,0:24:11.24,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So again, because\N{\rChinese}好的？再说一次，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.24,0:24:14.92,English,,0,0,0,,the Vikings never wrote anything down, we actually don't know\N{\rChinese}维京人从未曾记载，实际上我们并不知晓。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.92,0:24:17.04,English,,0,0,0,,that much about these funerals.\N{\rChinese}关于这些葬礼的事就到此为止。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.14,0:24:19.80,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, we only have one.\N{\rChinese}实际上我们只有一条记录。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.80,0:24:23.16,English,,0,0,0,,One historical record of a funeral.\N{\rChinese}一条关于葬礼的历史记录。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.66,0:24:27.46,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And this happened in the Viking Rus.\N{\rChinese}好的？这件事发生在维京鲁斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.58,0:24:30.76,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So this is Eastern, the Eastern world near the Volga.\N{\rChinese}好的？这就是东部，伏尔加附近的东部世界。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.34,0:24:36.06,English,,0,0,0,,And it was written down by a Muslim diplomat\N{\rChinese}并且这被一名穆斯林外交官记载。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.06,0:24:39.32,English,,0,0,0,,and traveler by the name of Ahmad ibn Badlan.\N{\rChinese}并且一名旅行者，名为阿赫马德·伊本·巴德兰。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.66,0:24:42.04,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And he is from the Abbasid Caliphate.\N{\rChinese}好？他来自阿拔斯王朝。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.90,0:24:47.92,English,,0,0,0,,And he is in the Viking world in order to negotiate a treaty of trade.\N{\rChinese}好？他来到维京世界，目的是谈判贸易条约。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.06,0:24:50.42,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The Abbasids and the Vikings traded a lot.\N{\rChinese}好的？阿拔斯王朝和维京人交易频繁。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.66,0:24:52.02,English,,0,0,0,,And as an honored guest,\N{\rChinese}而且作为贵宾，
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.32,0:24:58.14,English,,0,0,0,,the Vikings invited him to a funeral of a deceased chieftain or king.\N{\rChinese}维京人邀请他参加一位已故领袖或王的葬礼。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.54,0:25:03.14,English,,0,0,0,,All right? Now, there are certain things about this funeral that's important for us.\N{\rChinese}好的？现在，有些关于这场葬礼的事对我们很重要。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.28,0:25:06.18,English,,0,0,0,,The first thing is that it would last 10 days.\N{\rChinese}第一点是它会持续十天。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.62,0:25:09.34,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? It's a very elaborate affair that\N{\rChinese}好的？这是一场非常精心的仪式。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.34,0:25:12.70,English,,0,0,0,,requires a lot of choreography and coronation.\N{\rChinese}需要大量舞蹈与加冕。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.16,0:25:16.48,English,,0,0,0,,The second thing is that...\N{\rChinese}第二点是……
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.22,0:25:22.90,English,,0,0,0,,A third of the man's wealth was spent on the funeral expenses.\N{\rChinese}三分之一的财富用于葬礼费用。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.18,0:25:25.00,English,,0,0,0,,So basically, a feast for everyone.\N{\rChinese}所以基本上，大家都有盛宴。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.54,0:25:29.00,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? A third was spent on his funeral clothes\N{\rChinese}好吧？三分之一的费用用于他的葬礼服装。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.00,0:25:31.10,English,,0,0,0,,that was tailor -made for him.\N{\rChinese}那套服装是为他量身定做的。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.24,0:25:33.16,English,,0,0,0,,So this is like the best clothes.\N{\rChinese}于是这就是最好的衣服。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.44,0:25:36.22,English,,0,0,0,,And a third was given to his wife.\N{\rChinese}又有三分之一给了他的妻子。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.54,0:25:39.60,English,,0,0,0,,What this tells us is, first of all, this man,\N{\rChinese}这说明了，首先，这个人……
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.70,0:25:42.12,English,,0,0,0,,even though he was high status, he didn't have that much wealth.\N{\rChinese}即使他身份高贵，却并不富有。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.30,0:25:44.20,English,,0,0,0,,Right? And second of all,\N{\rChinese}对吧？其次，
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.28,0:25:47.28,English,,0,0,0,,the Vikings are a very egalitarian society.\N{\rChinese}维京人是个非常平等的社会。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.92,0:25:51.38,English,,0,0,0,,And the third thing that's important for us, they didn't care that much about wealth.\N{\rChinese}还有第三点很重要：他们并不太在意财富。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.48,0:25:53.12,English,,0,0,0,,Period. Right?\N{\rChinese}点。对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.78,0:25:55.76,English,,0,0,0,,They spent a third on the funeral.\N{\rChinese}他们在葬礼上花了三分之一。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.86,0:25:57.88,English,,0,0,0,,They just burned away the money.\N{\rChinese}他们把钱都烧掉了。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.28,0:25:59.74,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So\N{\rChinese}好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.74,0:26:03.94,English,,0,0,0,,what's also important for us to remember is there is a funeral director.\N{\rChinese}还有一点很重要：有个葬礼导演。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.26,0:26:05.90,English,,0,0,0,,There's a woman who\N{\rChinese}有个女人……
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.90,0:26:09.18,English,,0,0,0,,Ibn Fanlin calls the Angel of Death,\N{\rChinese}伊本·法林称之为死亡天使，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.42,0:26:13.54,English,,0,0,0,,who is coordinating and orchestrating this funeral.\N{\rChinese}他正在统筹并安排这场葬礼。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.78,0:26:17.26,English,,0,0,0,,During the course of this funeral, there are...\N{\rChinese}在葬礼进行期间，出现了……
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.26,0:26:19.58,English,,0,0,0,,There are things that happen that actually disgust him.\N{\rChinese}有些事发生了，真让他觉得好吃惊。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.92,0:26:22.44,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So before we continue,\N{\rChinese}好的？那我们继续之前，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.70,0:26:26.92,English,,0,0,0,,please keep in mind that Ibn Fanlin, he's an observer.\N{\rChinese}请记住伊本·法林是个观察者。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.30,0:26:29.76,English,,0,0,0,,He doesn't speak the language. He doesn't know culture.\N{\rChinese}他不会说这门话，也不懂这门文化。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.02,0:26:32.12,English,,0,0,0,,So he doesn't exactly know what's going on.\N{\rChinese}于是他不太清楚到底发生了什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.38,0:26:34.42,English,,0,0,0,,Second of all, he's a Muslim.\N{\rChinese}第二点，他是穆斯林。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.60,0:26:37.88,English,,0,0,0,,So he has his own cultural worldview that\N{\rChinese}于是他有自己的文化视角，且
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.88,0:26:41.08,English,,0,0,0,,is in conflict with the Viking worldview.\N{\rChinese}与维京视角相冲突。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.54,0:26:45.52,English,,0,0,0,,The third thing is he is writing this down after the fact.\N{\rChinese}第三点是他在事后把这写下来。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.52,0:26:48.40,English,,0,0,0,,And if you do that, what often happens is that\N{\rChinese}如果你这么做，往往会出现的情况是
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.40,0:26:50.70,English,,0,0,0,,you will misremember a lot of things.\N{\rChinese}你会记错很多事。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.94,0:26:56.12,English,,0,0,0,,So please take his description with a grain of salt,\N{\rChinese}请把他的描述当作参考，略加留意，稍加怀疑。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.20,0:27:00.58,English,,0,0,0,,with some skepticism. But also, please remember that we have no choice in the matter.\N{\rChinese}请记住，我们对此事没有选择。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.66,0:27:05.64,English,,0,0,0,,This is the only written record of a Viking funeral from this time.\N{\rChinese}这是该时期唯一的维京葬礼书面记录。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.96,0:27:08.86,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So we have absolutely no choice in the matter.\N{\rChinese}好的？我们对此事完全没有选择。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.00,0:27:11.62,English,,0,0,0,,So let's look at what he writes and then\N{\rChinese}于是我们先看他写的，然后再尝试重建维京文化。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.62,0:27:14.80,English,,0,0,0,,try to reconstruct the Viking culture.\N{\rChinese}接着我们再去重建维京文化。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.80,0:27:16.84,English,,0,0,0,,And understanding. Okay.\N{\rChinese}并且理解。好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.90,0:27:20.34,English,,0,0,0,,So first thing he says is, They cut a dog in two\N{\rChinese}首先他说的是：他们把一只狗切成两半。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.34,0:27:24.60,English,,0,0,0,,and threw the halves into the boat and placed the man's weapons beside him.\N{\rChinese}他们把两半扔进船里，并把人的武器放在他旁边。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.90,0:27:28.10,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So again, they are celebrating his life.\N{\rChinese}好的？所以又是他们在庆祝他的生命。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.20,0:27:29.46,English,,0,0,0,,They are memorizing his life.\N{\rChinese}他们正在记住他的生涯。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.46,0:27:33.62,English,,0,0,0,,They had two horses run themselves sweaty, cut them to pieces,\N{\rChinese}他们让两匹马自己跑到汗流满身，切成块状。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.72,0:27:35.72,English,,0,0,0,,and threw the meat into the ship.\N{\rChinese}把肉扔进船里。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.86,0:27:38.54,English,,0,0,0,,Finally, they killed two cows, a hen, and a cock and\N{\rChinese}最后，他们杀了两头牛、一只母鸡和一只公鸡，并同样处理它们。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.54,0:27:40.66,English,,0,0,0,,did the same with them.\N{\rChinese}did the same with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.78,0:27:44.16,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So not only are they remembering him, but they're giving him supplies.\N{\rChinese}好的吗？所以他们不仅在记住他，还给他补给。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.24,0:27:48.62,English,,0,0,0,,To help to sustain him as he ventures\N{\rChinese}为了帮助他在踏上旅程时维持。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.62,0:27:50.22,English,,0,0,0,,and voyages into the afterworld.\N{\rChinese}并航行进入来世。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.96,0:27:52.32,English,,0,0,0,,Now this is interesting.\N{\rChinese}现在这很有趣。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.48,0:27:53.98,English,,0,0,0,,They ask for a human sacrifice.\N{\rChinese}他们要人祭。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.42,0:27:56.62,English,,0,0,0,,And a slave girl volunteers.\N{\rChinese}一名奴女自愿。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.44,0:27:59.36,English,,0,0,0,,Volunteers. Okay? Clearly she didn't volunteer.\N{\rChinese}自愿。好的吗？显然她并未自愿。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.68,0:28:03.00,English,,0,0,0,,But she volunteers. And let's see what happens.\N{\rChinese}但她自愿。让我们看看会怎样。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.66,0:28:07.32,English,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, the slave girl went from one tent to the other\N{\rChinese}与此同时，奴女从一帐篷走到另一帐篷。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.32,0:28:10.44,English,,0,0,0,,and had sexual intercourse with the master of each.\N{\rChinese}与各自主人发生性关系。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.66,0:28:14.78,English,,0,0,0,,Every man told her, Tell your master that I have done this purely out of love.\N{\rChinese}每个男人对她说，告诉你的主人，我之所以做这件事完全是出于爱。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.78,0:28:16.10,English,,0,0,0,,I have done this out of love for you.\N{\rChinese}我之所以做这件事完全是出于对你的爱。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.22,0:28:18.08,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, it's not, this is incorrect.\N{\rChinese}好的，没错，这个是正确的。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.26,0:28:19.70,English,,0,0,0,,It should be for him. Alright?\N{\rChinese}应该是给他的。好了？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.80,0:28:21.88,English,,0,0,0,,So this is really confusing for us.\N{\rChinese}这对我们来说真的很困惑。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.34,0:28:26.54,English,,0,0,0,,It's a funeral and they're having sex with the woman\N{\rChinese}这是一场葬礼，他们正与即将被祭祀的女子发生性关系。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.54,0:28:31.20,English,,0,0,0,,who is about to be sacrificed. So we don't have, we have absolutely no idea what's going on.\N{\rChinese}于是我们完全不知道发生了什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.40,0:28:34.16,English,,0,0,0,,But I'm going to make a guess.\N{\rChinese}但我打算做个猜测。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.28,0:28:36.04,English,,0,0,0,,I'm going to use my imagination. Okay?\N{\rChinese}我打算用想象力。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.64,0:28:39.10,English,,0,0,0,,First, it's important for us to understand who the slave girl is.\N{\rChinese}首先，我们要弄清奴隶女孩是谁。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.78,0:28:41.00,English,,0,0,0,,She's not a normal person.\N{\rChinese}她不是普通人。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.74,0:28:43.64,English,,0,0,0,,I believe, I would argue that\N{\rChinese}我认为，我会说
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.64,0:28:48.08,English,,0,0,0,,she must be the lover of the deceased chieftain.\N{\rChinese}她一定是已故领袖的情人。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.32,0:28:49.64,English,,0,0,0,,Why? Okay.\N{\rChinese}为什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.46,0:28:54.52,English,,0,0,0,,Here's the logic. Um, remember the Iliad.\N{\rChinese}这里是逻辑。嗯，记得《伊利亚特》吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.68,0:28:56.04,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? In the Iliad,\N{\rChinese}好？在《伊利亚特》中，
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.16,0:29:01.08,English,,0,0,0,,the entire story begins with a problem.\N{\rChinese}整个故事从一个问题开始。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.28,0:29:04.48,English,,0,0,0,,The problem is that Agamemnon, the leader of the Greeks,\N{\rChinese}问题是，阿伽门农，希腊人之首领，
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.62,0:29:07.28,English,,0,0,0,,he has kidnapped a girl\N{\rChinese}他绑走了一个女孩
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.28,0:29:11.40,English,,0,0,0,,who happens to be the daughter of a high priest, Apolo.\N{\rChinese}她恰好是高祭司阿波罗的女儿
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.02,0:29:14.62,English,,0,0,0,,And the king, and the priest comes to him and says,\N{\rChinese}王和祭司来找他说，
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.20,0:29:19.18,English,,0,0,0,,I will give you all the gold in the world, but please give me back my daughter.\N{\rChinese}我会把天下所有黄金都给你，但请把我的女儿还给我。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.84,0:29:23.00,English,,0,0,0,,And all the Greeks are said, Oh, you should do that, Agamemnon.\N{\rChinese}于是众希腊人说，阿伽门农，你就这么做吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.22,0:29:24.70,English,,0,0,0,,Please give back the daughter.\N{\rChinese}请把女儿还给我。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.88,0:29:26.64,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? That's just the custom of war.\N{\rChinese}好的？这就是战争的习俗。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.22,0:29:29.82,English,,0,0,0,,If a father can ransom the daughter, you have to return her.\N{\rChinese}若父亲能赎回女儿，你就得还给她。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.16,0:29:31.60,English,,0,0,0,,But Agamemnon says this,\N{\rChinese}但阿伽门农说：
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.18,0:29:35.16,English,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to return her because I love her.\N{\rChinese}我不打算还给她，因为我爱她。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.56,0:29:37.22,English,,0,0,0,,I love her more than my wife.\N{\rChinese}我比爱她还爱我的妻子。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.72,0:29:43.70,English,,0,0,0,,And as a result, the high priest prays to Apolo,\N{\rChinese}于是大祭司向阿波罗祈祷，
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.86,0:29:46.88,English,,0,0,0,,who unleashes a deadly plague among the Greeks.\N{\rChinese}阿波罗随即在希腊人中掀起致命瘟疫。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.00,0:29:50.62,English,,0,0,0,,The Greeks are dying. So finally, Achilles steps up\N{\rChinese}希腊人相继垂命。于是阿基琉斯终于上场。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.62,0:29:53.92,English,,0,0,0,,and says to Agamemnon, you have to return the girl.\N{\rChinese}并对阿伽门农说，你得把女孩送回去。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.84,0:29:57.60,English,,0,0,0,,All right? Now, Agamemnon has lost faith.\N{\rChinese}好的？现在，阿伽门农失去了信心。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.84,0:30:01.64,English,,0,0,0,,So he says to Achilles, fine, I will return the girl\N{\rChinese}于是他对阿基琉斯说，好的，我会把女孩送回去。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.64,0:30:04.38,English,,0,0,0,,that I love more than anything else in the world, but\N{\rChinese}我爱它胜过世间万物，但你必须把你的奴女送给我。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.38,0:30:07.44,English,,0,0,0,,you must give me your girl, your slave girl.\N{\rChinese}于是阿基琉斯对此大为愤怒。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.74,0:30:10.94,English,,0,0,0,,And Achilles gets so angry about this,\N{\rChinese}And Achilles getsso angry about this,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.90,0:30:14.80,English,,0,0,0,,that he refused to fight for the Greeks,\N{\rChinese}他拒绝为希腊作战，于是特洛伊战争的灾祸就此而起。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.92,0:30:17.46,English,,0,0,0,,which leads to the disaster of the Trojan War.\N{\rChinese}好了？那这又告诉我们什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.02,0:30:19.64,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So what is this telling us?\N{\rChinese}Okay? So what isthis telling us?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.70,0:30:22.44,English,,0,0,0,,This is telling us that in this world,\N{\rChinese}这告诉我们，在这个世界里，
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.94,0:30:24.80,English,,0,0,0,,where these men are far from home,\N{\rChinese}在这些人离家很远的地方，
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.78,0:30:28.14,English,,0,0,0,,and they kidnap these slave girls,\N{\rChinese}他们绑架这些奴女。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.82,0:30:30.26,English,,0,0,0,,they fall in love with them.\N{\rChinese}他们与之相恋。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.10,0:30:33.26,English,,0,0,0,,And in the process of falling in love with them,\N{\rChinese}在相恋的过程中，
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.38,0:30:37.54,English,,0,0,0,,these great men confer status and power onto these slave girls.\N{\rChinese}这些伟人赋予奴女地位与权力。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.76,0:30:40.12,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, does that make sense? All right?\N{\rChinese}好的，听得懂吗？行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.12,0:30:41.88,English,,0,0,0,,I know this is hard to understand, but\N{\rChinese}我知道这很难懂，但
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.88,0:30:45.30,English,,0,0,0,,the slave girl is not a normal girl.\N{\rChinese}奴女不是普通女孩。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.54,0:30:47.58,English,,0,0,0,,She is the lover, the mistress,\N{\rChinese}她是情人，女主人，本质是已逝首领的妻子。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.84,0:30:52.68,English,,0,0,0,,essentially the wife of the chieftain who's died.\N{\rChinese}好？于是又一问：她为何自愿自杀？
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.26,0:30:59.16,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So another question then is, why has she volunteered to kill herself?\N{\rChinese}Okay? So another question then is, why has she volunteered to kill herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.50,0:31:03.36,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, well, if we continue the logic, then I would argue that it's because\N{\rChinese}好的，继续推理，我认为是因为
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.96,0:31:07.74,English,,0,0,0,,without the man, she has no status and power in the community.\N{\rChinese}没有那个人，她在社区里就没有地位和陆权。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.74,0:31:10.20,English,,0,0,0,,She'll go back to being a slave,\N{\rChinese}她会回到奴隶的身份。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.96,0:31:12.70,English,,0,0,0,,and she might be ostracized.\N{\rChinese}并且她可能被放逐。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.14,0:31:16.86,English,,0,0,0,,So by volunteering and sacrificing herself,\N{\rChinese}于是自愿并牺自我，
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.76,0:31:20.84,English,,0,0,0,,she will win status and power and\N{\rChinese}她将赢得地位与陆权。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.84,0:31:25.10,English,,0,0,0,,honor for her children and for her relatives in the community.\N{\rChinese}为子孙和亲属赢得荣誉。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.34,0:31:27.78,English,,0,0,0,,She will make her family part of that community.\N{\rChinese}她会把家人纳入社区。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.18,0:31:29.68,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? That's why she does this.\N{\rChinese}好？这就是她这么做的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.52,0:31:33.96,English,,0,0,0,,Now then the question then is, okay, I don't get it now,\N{\rChinese}现在问题是，我现在不明白，
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.08,0:31:37.72,English,,0,0,0,,because if in fact the slave girl is a slave,\N{\rChinese}如果这位奴隶女孩确实是奴隶，
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.72,0:31:42.10,English,,0,0,0,,the chieftain's favorite mistress, and\N{\rChinese}酋长的宠妾
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.10,0:31:45.04,English,,0,0,0,,if this slave girl does\N{\rChinese}如果这位奴隶女孩真的做了
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.04,0:31:48.80,English,,0,0,0,,in fact love this man,\N{\rChinese}如果这位奴隶女孩真的爱上了这位男子
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.04,0:31:50.98,English,,0,0,0,,why is she having sex with everyone?\N{\rChinese}她为什么要和大家做事？
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.92,0:31:54.76,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, and the answer is,\N{\rChinese}好的，答案是，
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.30,0:32:02.08,English,,0,0,0,,in this world, gifts are very important.\N{\rChinese}在这个世界里，礼物非常重要。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.54,0:32:05.62,English,,0,0,0,,Basically if you go to war and you win things, you have to share it with everyone.\N{\rChinese}基本上你去打仗赢得东西后，得与大家分享。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.88,0:32:08.80,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So what this deceased man is saying, now that\N{\rChinese}好的？那么这位已故去的男子现在说什么呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.80,0:32:10.72,English,,0,0,0,,I'm dead, I give you one final gift.\N{\rChinese}我已去世，送你一份终极礼物。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.96,0:32:14.18,English,,0,0,0,,And it's the greatest treasure that I can possibly give you,\N{\rChinese}这就是我能送给你的最大宝藏。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.26,0:32:16.46,English,,0,0,0,,which is the woman I love.\N{\rChinese}我爱上的女人是她。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.44,0:32:22.04,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And that's why each man is forced to have sex with her.\N{\rChinese}好？所以每个男人都被迫与她做事。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.12,0:32:25.96,English,,0,0,0,,And they tell this girl, when you go to your master,\N{\rChinese}他们告诉这女孩，当你去你主人的时候。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.62,0:32:32.04,English,,0,0,0,,tell him, I only do this out of my love for him,\N{\rChinese}告诉他，我只是出于对他的爱才这么做，不是为了你。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.20,0:32:33.96,English,,0,0,0,,not for you. I don't have sex with you.\N{\rChinese}我和你没有交往。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.04,0:32:36.06,English,,0,0,0,,I do not want to have sex with you.\N{\rChinese}我也不想跟你交往。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.18,0:32:39.54,English,,0,0,0,,But I will in order to celebrate him,\N{\rChinese}但我会为了庆祝他而做，
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.70,0:32:41.86,English,,0,0,0,,to honor him, to love him.\N{\rChinese}为了敬他，爱他。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.04,0:32:57.18,English,,0,0,0,,Yes? So, June, that's a great question.\N{\rChinese}是吗？所以，六月，这是个好问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.92,0:33:00.26,English,,0,0,0,,In their imagination, are they having sex with the dead master?\N{\rChinese}在他们的想象里，他们和已故主相交吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.62,0:33:05.70,English,,0,0,0,,And, yes. You can make that argument, okay?\N{\rChinese}是的。你可以这么说，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.18,0:33:07.42,English,,0,0,0,,Because remember, in this world,\N{\rChinese}因为记得，在这个世界里…
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.86,0:33:10.44,English,,0,0,0,,homosexuality is not, it doesn't exist.\N{\rChinese}同性恋不是，存在的。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.90,0:33:12.94,English,,0,0,0,,It's very, it's okay for men to have sex with each other.\N{\rChinese}很好，男人之间可以做爱。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.44,0:33:18.12,English,,0,0,0,,It's okay for men to have sex with, together with one woman.\N{\rChinese}男人之间可以做爱，也可以和一个女人一起做爱。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.24,0:33:21.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And that's how they create intimacy and bonding.\N{\rChinese}好的？这就是他们创造亲密与联结的方式。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.56,0:33:23.06,English,,0,0,0,,Because remember, when you're out in war,\N{\rChinese}因为记得，当你在战场上，
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.78,0:33:25.96,English,,0,0,0,,you have to be able to make the ultimate sacrifice.\N{\rChinese}你必须能作出终极牺牲。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.60,0:33:30.00,English,,0,0,0,,So you have to bond with your fellow soldiers.\N{\rChinese}于是你要与战友结缘。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.26,0:33:32.64,English,,0,0,0,,And the best way to bond is through sex.\N{\rChinese}最好的结缘方式就是交配。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.34,0:33:37.98,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Sex with each other, but also sex with other women.\N{\rChinese}好？互相交配，也可与他人交配。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.12,0:33:40.54,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, so, yeah.\N{\rChinese}好的？所以，嗯，没错。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.80,0:33:42.22,English,,0,0,0,,So you can make that argument, okay?\N{\rChinese}这样你就能提出那个论点，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.56,0:33:44.40,English,,0,0,0,,Again, I don't know what goes on in their heads.\N{\rChinese}再说一次，我不知道他们脑子里想的是什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.92,0:33:49.02,English,,0,0,0,,But if you extend the logic, yes, then they think they're having sex with the master.\N{\rChinese}但如果你把逻辑延伸，没错，那他们就认为自己在和主人做爱。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.18,0:33:52.42,English,,0,0,0,,For the girl. Alright?\N{\rChinese}给女孩的。好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.54,0:33:56.22,English,,0,0,0,,And that's why they say, I'm already doing this out of my love for,\N{\rChinese}这就是他们说的原因，我已经因为爱而这么做了。
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.84,0:33:58.80,English,,0,0,0,,for him. Not for you, but for him.\N{\rChinese}为他准备的。不是为你，而是为他。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.66,0:34:05.22,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Um, so let's continue, okay?\N{\rChinese}好吧？嗯，接着说，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.34,0:34:09.24,English,,0,0,0,,In the afternoon, they moved the slave girl to something that\N{\rChinese}下午，他们把奴女移到……
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.24,0:34:13.62,English,,0,0,0,,looked like a doorframe, where she was lifted on the palms of the man three times.\N{\rChinese}看起来像门框，她被那男人的手掌抬起三次。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.80,0:34:16.86,English,,0,0,0,,So the doorframe represents access to the afterworld.\N{\rChinese}于是门框象征通往来世的通道。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.94,0:34:18.90,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So she's being sacrificed now.\N{\rChinese}好了？现在她正被祭献。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.44,0:34:21.96,English,,0,0,0,,The first time, she saw her father and mother.\N{\rChinese}第一次，她看见了父亲和母亲。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.18,0:34:24.46,English,,0,0,0,,The second time, she saw all her deceased relatives.\N{\rChinese}第二次，她看见了所有已故去的亲属。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.78,0:34:27.58,English,,0,0,0,,And the third time, she saw her master in paradise.\N{\rChinese}第三次，她看见了她的主人在天堂。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.26,0:34:31.50,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So what this is, is she,\N{\rChinese}好了？这就是她，
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.58,0:34:35.38,English,,0,0,0,,the slave girl, who is not, who is not part of the community.\N{\rChinese}奴隶女孩，未曾成为社区的一员。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.60,0:34:37.72,English,,0,0,0,,What she's really doing is implanting\N{\rChinese}她真正做的事是植入。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.72,0:34:42.92,English,,0,0,0,,her personal memory into the community as a whole.\N{\rChinese}把她的个人记忆融入整个社区。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.08,0:34:45.42,English,,0,0,0,,She's making her family part of the community now.\N{\rChinese}她把家族纳入社区。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.92,0:34:47.70,English,,0,0,0,,Right? She's talking about her past.\N{\rChinese}对吧？她在谈她的过去。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.98,0:34:51.02,English,,0,0,0,,And everyone, again, this is a community event, everyone's observing.\N{\rChinese}又一次，大家都在场合，人人都在观赏。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.34,0:34:52.64,English,,0,0,0,,Everyone can hear her.\N{\rChinese}人人都能听见她的声音。
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.42,0:34:55.56,English,,0,0,0,,Alright? So they know that after she dies,\N{\rChinese}好了？所以他们知道她死后，
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.70,0:35:00.02,English,,0,0,0,,they must honor her memory by honoring her relatives and family.\N{\rChinese}他们必须以祭祀亲属和家族来纪念她。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.16,0:35:03.70,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? There it was green\N{\rChinese}好了？那时是绿色的。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.70,0:35:06.72,English,,0,0,0,,and beautiful, and together with him, she saw men and young people.\N{\rChinese}又美丽，和他一起，她看见了男人和年轻人。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.82,0:35:09.46,English,,0,0,0,,She saw her master beckon for her, and\N{\rChinese}她看见主人招手给她，随后被送来一只鸡，她把鸡宰了，随后把它投进船里。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.46,0:35:12.66,English,,0,0,0,,she was brought a chicken, which she, which she decasipated,\N{\rChinese}她看见主人招手给她，随后被送来一只鸡，她宰了鸡，随后把它投进船里。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.82,0:35:14.48,English,,0,0,0,,and which was then thrown on the boat.\N{\rChinese}她看见主人招手给她，随后被送来一只鸡，她宰了鸡，随后把它投进船里。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.56,0:35:17.20,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Again, this is some, some strange ritual that\N{\rChinese}好的？这又是某种奇怪的仪式，我不明白它的意义，但一定有其含义。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.20,0:35:20.38,English,,0,0,0,,I have no idea what it means, but it must mean something.\N{\rChinese}好的？他们常做的事是重现神话。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.50,0:35:24.64,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Often what they do is, they reenact mythologies.\N{\rChinese}好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.78,0:35:26.40,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So there must have been a famous story\N{\rChinese}好的？那一定有一段著名的故事
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.98,0:35:29.72,English,,0,0,0,,where a woman decapitates a chicken for some reason.\N{\rChinese}在那段故事里，一位女子因某种缘由宰鸡头
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.82,0:35:32.70,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And she's doing that. There are reliving mythologies.\N{\rChinese}好的？她正是这么做的，正是重现神话
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.40,0:35:36.94,English,,0,0,0,,Alright, let's continue. Thereafter, the slave girl was taken away to the ship.\N{\rChinese}好的，继续。随后奴隶女孩被送上船。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.12,0:35:40.40,English,,0,0,0,,She removed her bracelets and gave them to the old woman.\N{\rChinese}她把手镯取下，递给老女人。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.60,0:35:43.28,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? She took what was most valuable to her and\N{\rChinese}好的？她拿走了最珍贵的东西。
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.28,0:35:46.22,English,,0,0,0,,gave her to the old woman who was the angel of death, the funeral director.\N{\rChinese}把她交给了那位负责葬礼的老女人，她是死亡的天使。
