Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.66,0:42:49.96,English,,0,0,0,,But once he drank from the well and learned cosmic knowledge,\N{\rChinese}但一旦他喝下井水并获得宇宙知识，
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.16,0:42:52.48,English,,0,0,0,,he became more curious about the universe.\N{\rChinese}他对宇宙产生了更深的好奇。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.80,0:42:55.30,English,,0,0,0,,And so he started to venture into more unknowns.\N{\rChinese}于是他开始探索更多未知。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.66,0:42:58.38,English,,0,0,0,,Eventually he went into the realm of death.\N{\rChinese}最终他进入了死亡的境界。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.98,0:43:02.16,English,,0,0,0,,And no matter how hard he tried, he could not penetrate this world.\N{\rChinese}无论他多么努力，都无法穿透这个世界。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.34,0:43:04.82,English,,0,0,0,,There were too many winds, there were too many barriers.\N{\rChinese}风太多，障碍也太多。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.56,0:43:08.98,English,,0,0,0,,So he killed himself, right?\N{\rChinese}于是他自杀了，对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.06,0:43:11.94,English,,0,0,0,,Because that's what you do. If you want to enter a death world, you have to kill yourself.\N{\rChinese}因为这就是你要做的事。如果你想进入死亡之境，你就得自杀。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.16,0:43:14.58,English,,0,0,0,,So he killed himself and was dead for a long time.\N{\rChinese}于是他自杀，随后长时间沉睡。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.78,0:43:18.80,English,,0,0,0,,But in his death, he was able to see all the secrets of the universe.\N{\rChinese}在那段死亡中，他得以洞察宇宙万秘。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.26,0:43:21.30,English,,0,0,0,,And then afterwards he resurrected himself.\N{\rChinese}然后他又复活了。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.78,0:43:26.02,English,,0,0,0,,So Odin personifies the idea of courage in the Viking world.\N{\rChinese}于是奥丁在维京世界里化身为勇气的化身。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.34,0:43:28.82,English,,0,0,0,,To seek the unknown relentlessly.\N{\rChinese}不懈追寻未知。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.50,0:43:32.50,English,,0,0,0,,Even if it costs you your life and your eye.\N{\rChinese}即使付出生命与双眼。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.70,0:43:37.20,English,,0,0,0,,The idea of loyalty.\N{\rChinese}忠诚之意。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.90,0:43:40.18,English,,0,0,0,,So Um,\N{\rChinese}嗯，
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.48,0:43:45.18,English,,0,0,0,,in the Norse world there'd be a Ragnarok.\N{\rChinese}在北欧世界里会有一次罗格纳罗克。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.60,0:43:48.90,English,,0,0,0,,And there's a wolf, Fenris,\N{\rChinese}还有一只狼，芬里斯。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.12,0:43:52.08,English,,0,0,0,,who will um,\N{\rChinese}谁将会，
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.36,0:43:54.74,English,,0,0,0,,foreshadow the arrival of Ragnarok.\N{\rChinese}预示罗格纳罗克的到来。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.78,0:43:58.56,English,,0,0,0,,He's very dangerous. But when he's born, he's just a little pup.\N{\rChinese}他很危险。但刚出生时只是小狗。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.84,0:44:00.84,English,,0,0,0,,So the Essar, the gods,\N{\rChinese}于是埃萨尔，众神，
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.10,0:44:05.98,English,,0,0,0,,um basically decide to adopt him as a pet.\N{\rChinese}嗯基本决定把他当宠物养。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.20,0:44:09.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? They think he's harmless. And his master is Tyr, who is the king.\N{\rChinese}好的？他们认为他无害。主宰是特尔，国王。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.38,0:44:11.22,English,,0,0,0,,the god of war among the Aesir.\N{\rChinese}战神，阿斯神族中的战争之神。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.16,0:44:16.56,English,,0,0,0,,But very quickly, Fenris grows to be huge.\N{\rChinese}很快，芬里斯长大成巨。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.80,0:44:18.44,English,,0,0,0,,And now the gods see him as a menace.\N{\rChinese}于是众神把他视为威胁。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.74,0:44:19.96,English,,0,0,0,,So they try to tie him up.\N{\rChinese}于是他们试着把他绑住。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.22,0:44:21.74,English,,0,0,0,,But no matter how hard they try,\N{\rChinese}不管他们多努力，
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.24,0:44:24.86,English,,0,0,0,,they can't tie him up. And it becomes like a game.\N{\rChinese}他们绑不住他，变成一场游戏。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.78,0:44:27.66,English,,0,0,0,,And Fenris thinks this is really funny.\N{\rChinese}芬里斯觉得这真好玩。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.20,0:44:31.50,English,,0,0,0,,But the gods become really worried, so they go to the dwarves.\N{\rChinese}于是众神很担心，去请矮人帮忙。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.70,0:44:36.46,English,,0,0,0,,And they ask the dwarves to create a magic rope, which they do.\N{\rChinese}于是他们请矮人制造一根魔法绳，矮人就做了。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.00,0:44:39.70,English,,0,0,0,,And Tyr goes back to Fenris and says, Hey,\N{\rChinese}于是提尔回到芬里斯那里说，嘿，
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.88,0:44:44.64,English,,0,0,0,,let's continue this game of us trying to tie you up.\N{\rChinese}我们继续玩这场绑住你的游戏吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.20,0:44:48.82,English,,0,0,0,,Fenris is like, okay. But how do I know\N{\rChinese}芬里斯说：好的。那我怎么知道你会放我出去？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.82,0:44:52.26,English,,0,0,0,,that you'll release me if I can't get out?\N{\rChinese}这里，把你的手放进我的嘴里。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.00,0:44:56.06,English,,0,0,0,,Here, put your hand in my mouth.\N{\rChinese}Here, put your hand in my mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.66,0:44:58.82,English,,0,0,0,,And if you don't release me, I'll take your hand.\N{\rChinese}如果你不放我，我就把你的手拿走。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.88,0:45:01.66,English,,0,0,0,,So the gods discuss this.\N{\rChinese}于是众神讨论此事。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.22,0:45:05.54,English,,0,0,0,,And Tyr volunteers to do this.\N{\rChinese}于是提尔自愿去做这件事。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.58,0:45:08.62,English,,0,0,0,,Knowing. That he's going to lose his hand.\N{\rChinese}知道他会失去手。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.62,0:45:11.02,English,,0,0,0,,And that's what happens.\N{\rChinese}于是就这样了。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.12,0:45:12.66,English,,0,0,0,,They tie Fenris up.\N{\rChinese}他们把芬里斯绑住。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.88,0:45:14.88,English,,0,0,0,,And Fenris wants to be released.\N{\rChinese}而芬里斯想要被释放。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.94,0:45:16.64,English,,0,0,0,,The gods refuse because he's a menace.\N{\rChinese}众神拒绝，因为他是威胁。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.80,0:45:19.88,English,,0,0,0,,And then Fenris just cuts off,\N{\rChinese}随后芬里斯就把手剪掉。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.94,0:45:22.40,English,,0,0,0,,bites off the hand.\N{\rChinese}咬掉手。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.58,0:45:26.92,English,,0,0,0,,That's the idea of loyalty. Loyalty to your friends.\N{\rChinese}这就是忠诚的意义。对朋友的忠诚。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.64,0:45:36.14,English,,0,0,0,,Resourcefulness. So the gods are always at war with the frost giants.\N{\rChinese}机智。于是众神总是与霜巨人交战。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.64,0:45:39.94,English,,0,0,0,,One day, a man named the Builder comes to them\N{\rChinese}一天，一个叫建造者的男人来到了他们那里
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.94,0:45:44.24,English,,0,0,0,,and says, I can build you a wall to protect you from your enemies.\N{\rChinese}他说，我可以给你们建一堵墙，保护你们免受敌人之害
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.62,0:45:49.24,English,,0,0,0,,In 18 months. This is Asgard, the home of the gods.\N{\rChinese}在十八个月里。这就是阿斯加德，众神的故乡
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.70,0:45:51.94,English,,0,0,0,,And the Builder says,\N{\rChinese}于是建造者说，
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.30,0:45:54.50,English,,0,0,0,,I will do this, but I want three things.\N{\rChinese}我会做到的，但我想要三件事。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.62,0:45:56.82,English,,0,0,0,,I want the sun. I want the moon.\N{\rChinese}我想要太阳，我想要月亮。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.00,0:46:01.04,English,,0,0,0,,I want the beautiful goddess Freyja in marriage.\N{\rChinese}我想把美丽的女神弗雷雅嫁给他。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.94,0:46:06.44,English,,0,0,0,,And Odin the god's like, no, that's a stupid deal. But local gods are like, no, that's not what I want.\N{\rChinese}奥丁这位神说，呃，算了，还是个糟的交易。当地的神们也说，呃，算了，还是个糟的交易。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.14,0:46:12.94,English,,0,0,0,,In one hundred years,\N{\rChinese}一百年后，
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.28,0:46:16.28,English,,0,0,0,,one hundred years, one hundred years, one hundred years,\N{\rChinese}一百年，一百年，一百年，
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.54,0:46:19.34,English,,0,0,0,,one hundred years, one hundred years, one hundred years, one hundred years, one hundred years, one hundred years, one hundred years, one hundred years, one hundred years,\N{\rChinese}一百年，一百年，一百年，一百年，一百年，一百年，一百年，一百年，一百年，
