Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.52,0:56:40.90,English,,0,0,0,,Some important things to know about this.\N{\rChinese}一些关于这件事的重要信息。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.06,0:56:43.32,English,,0,0,0,,First is the halls were huge.\N{\rChinese}首先，厅堂非常巨大。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.92,0:56:46.76,English,,0,0,0,,They were as huge as a Greek amphitheater.\N{\rChinese}它们的规模与希腊圆形剧场相当。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.90,0:56:50.10,English,,0,0,0,,So you could seat about 1,000, 2,000 people within the hall.\N{\rChinese}因此，你可以在大厅里容纳大约一千、两千人。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.14,0:56:53.48,English,,0,0,0,,Second is that you have dark rooms.\N{\rChinese}第二点是你们有黑暗的房间。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.50,0:56:56.22,English,,0,0,0,,You have darkness. When it's dark and you can't see,\N{\rChinese}你们有黑暗。当黑暗时你看不见。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.40,0:57:00.02,English,,0,0,0,,your ears become much more perceptive.\N{\rChinese}你的耳朵变得更敏锐。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.24,0:57:03.90,English,,0,0,0,,So the words have become alive.\N{\rChinese}于是词语便活了起来。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.24,0:57:06.66,English,,0,0,0,,They're more colored, they're more detailed, they're much more imagery.\N{\rChinese}它们更有色彩，更细腻，更具画面感。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.10,0:57:09.54,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And\N{\rChinese}好了？
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.54,0:57:14.84,English,,0,0,0,,third is these words are bouncing off the walls\N{\rChinese}第三点是这些词语在墙壁上弹跳，
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.84,0:57:16.34,English,,0,0,0,,and they're creating echo and resonance.\N{\rChinese}它们产生回声与共振。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.84,0:57:20.12,English,,0,0,0,,And so these words almost like bonds\N{\rChinese}于是这些词语几乎像纽带
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.12,0:57:23.30,English,,0,0,0,,that unite everyone in the telling of the story.\N{\rChinese}把大家在叙述故事时连在一起。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.96,0:57:26.50,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And if you think about it,\N{\rChinese}好了？如果你想想看，
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.60,0:57:31.64,English,,0,0,0,,this experience is very similar to the Ice Age.\N{\rChinese}这次经历和冰河时代很相似。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.98,0:57:34.12,English,,0,0,0,,Remember last semester at the very beginning,\N{\rChinese}记得上学期刚开始时，
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.26,0:57:36.80,English,,0,0,0,,we did the Ice Age cave paintings.\N{\rChinese}我们做了冰河时代的洞穴壁画。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.42,0:57:40.70,English,,0,0,0,,And what we need to understand is people came together\N{\rChinese}于是我们需要理解的是，人们聚集在这些洞穴里不是为了绘画，
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.19,0:57:46.90,English,,0,0,0,,in these caves not to paint in the caves,\N{\rChinese}而是为了讲述他们来自何方的故事。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.58,0:57:51.30,English,,0,0,0,,but to tell stories about where they came from.\N{\rChinese}but to tell stories about where they came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.46,0:57:53.86,English,,0,0,0,,Who they are and where they're going.\N{\rChinese}他们是谁，他们去向何方。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.74,0:57:57.32,English,,0,0,0,,All right? And\N{\rChinese}好的？还有
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.32,0:58:01.08,English,,0,0,0,,all of our ancestors, every one of them for thousands of years,\N{\rChinese}我们所有的祖先，千百年来的每一个。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.22,0:58:06.92,English,,0,0,0,,participated in this process of converging in these ice caves\N{\rChinese}参与了在这些冰洞中聚合的过程
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.46,0:58:12.00,English,,0,0,0,,and hearing stories being told to them in these dark, wet caves.\N{\rChinese}并在这些黑暗、潮湿的洞穴里听到被讲述的故事
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.52,0:58:17.06,English,,0,0,0,,So this takes us back to the time of the Ice Age.\N{\rChinese}于是我们回到冰河时代
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.12,0:58:19.70,English,,0,0,0,,It's activating a nostalgia within us.\N{\rChinese}它在我们心中激起一股怀旧之情。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.76,0:58:21.44,English,,0,0,0,,And that's why the oral tradition is important.\N{\rChinese}这正是口述传统重要的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.44,0:58:23.24,English,,0,0,0,,It's so powerful. Okay?\N{\rChinese}它如此强大，懂了吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.94,0:58:30.32,English,,0,0,0,,All right. So these stories have been told in a certain way\N{\rChinese}好的。于是这些故事以某种方式被讲述
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.66,0:58:33.30,English,,0,0,0,,to excite the audience.\N{\rChinese}以激发听众的情绪。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.94,0:58:35.22,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so think of this class.\N{\rChinese}好了，想象一下这门课。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.54,0:58:37.32,English,,0,0,0,,In this class, we have no tests.\N{\rChinese}在这门课里，我们没有考试。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.60,0:58:39.90,English,,0,0,0,,I don't even take attendance. So when\N{\rChinese}我甚至不记点名。于是当
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.90,0:58:41.94,English,,0,0,0,,I present material in this class,\N{\rChinese}我在这门课上呈现材料时
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.12,0:58:45.86,English,,0,0,0,,it has to be interesting for you, right?\N{\rChinese}它得让你觉得有趣，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.26,0:58:48.98,English,,0,0,0,,Why is it interesting? Because it's shocking.\N{\rChinese}为什么有趣？因为它很震撼。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.24,0:58:51.32,English,,0,0,0,,It has emotions. It has structure.\N{\rChinese}它有情感。它有结构。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.44,0:58:55.26,English,,0,0,0,,When I come to class, I actually do not script out my class.\N{\rChinese}当我上课时，我实际上并没有把课排成脚本。
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.66,0:59:00.04,English,,0,0,0,,What I do is I think of the narrative structure, the story I want to tell.\N{\rChinese}我所做的是先想好叙事结构，想好我要讲的故事。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.48,0:59:01.70,English,,0,0,0,,And then in class,\N{\rChinese}然后在课堂上，
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.34,0:59:06.18,English,,0,0,0,,depending on your reactions, depending on the question you ask,\N{\rChinese}根据你的反应，或者你提出的问题，
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.36,0:59:10.60,English,,0,0,0,,I will change some of the details in\N{\rChinese}我会在故事里改动一些细节，
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.60,0:59:12.84,English,,0,0,0,,the story to make it much more interesting for you.\N{\rChinese}让它更适合你，变得更有趣味。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.44,0:59:17.86,English,,0,0,0,,In the oral tradition, it's a co -creation, collaborative process.\N{\rChinese}在口头传统中，它是一种共同创作、协作的过程。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.18,0:59:19.84,English,,0,0,0,,And that's what makes it so powerful.\N{\rChinese}这正是它如此强大的原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.48,0:59:23.56,English,,0,0,0,,As an experiment, what you can do is this.\N{\rChinese}作为一次实验，你可以这样做。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.46,0:59:25.68,English,,0,0,0,,Think about this.\N{\rChinese}想一想这个。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.20,0:59:30.02,English,,0,0,0,,In class, there might be some material you found really interesting, right?\N{\rChinese}在课堂上，你可能会发现一些很有趣的材料，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.32,0:59:31.66,English,,0,0,0,,So then you go on YouTube.\N{\rChinese}于是你去YouTube。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.78,0:59:37.20,English,,0,0,0,,I post these lectures on YouTube to try to remember the experience.\N{\rChinese}我把这些讲座上传到YouTube，试着记住那段经历。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.48,0:59:38.98,English,,0,0,0,,And what you will find is you cannot.\N{\rChinese}你会发现，你还是记不住。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.72,0:59:43.14,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Because we've switched from oral culture to visual culture.\N{\rChinese}因为我们已从口头文化转向视觉文化。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.50,0:59:46.34,English,,0,0,0,,The same is true if it's your birthday, okay?\N{\rChinese}同样的道理也适用于你的生日，明白吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.50,0:59:48.52,English,,0,0,0,,It's your 18th birthday. You go out with your friends.\N{\rChinese}今天是你18岁的生日。你和朋友们一起出去。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.30,0:59:50.98,English,,0,0,0,,And you have a wonderful time.\N{\rChinese}你玩得很开心。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.28,0:59:53.82,English,,0,0,0,,And you're like, I want to take a picture to remember this experience.\N{\rChinese}我想拍张照来记住这段经历。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.48,0:59:56.74,English,,0,0,0,,But what you will find when you do that is\N{\rChinese}你会发现，当你这么做时，
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.50,1:00:00.84,English,,0,0,0,,the picture doesn't really capture the experience for you.\N{\rChinese}照片并没有真正捕捉住那段经历。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.60,1:00:04.80,English,,0,0,0,,The picture cannot bring back the feeling for you.\N{\rChinese}照片无法把那种感觉带回给你。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.46,1:00:07.66,English,,0,0,0,,And that's why the Vikings were so insistent\N{\rChinese}这就是为什么维京人如此坚持保持口头传统。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.18,1:00:10.12,English,,0,0,0,,on maintaining their oral tradition\N{\rChinese}on maintaining their oral tradition
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.20,1:00:14.76,English,,0,0,0,,and not transitioning into the literary culture.\N{\rChinese}并且未过渡到文学文化。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.34,1:00:19.72,English,,0,0,0,,Because their oral tradition is what gave the community purpose and meaning.\N{\rChinese}因为他们的口头传统给了社区目的和意义。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.96,1:00:23.78,English,,0,0,0,,If you gave that up, then your community would lose cohesiveness.\N{\rChinese}若你放弃它，社区就会失去凝聚力。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.36,1:00:28.16,English,,0,0,0,,Right? Does it make sense to you guys?\N{\rChinese}对吧？你们听得懂吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.38,1:00:32.54,English,,0,0,0,,All right. So what's the oral tradition?\N{\rChinese}好的。那么口头传统是什么？
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.06,1:00:34.38,English,,0,0,0,,Again, we've lost it.\N{\rChinese}再说一次，我们已经失去它了。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.70,1:00:36.02,English,,0,0,0,,We've mainly lost it.\N{\rChinese}我们主要失去它了。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.12,1:00:37.86,English,,0,0,0,,But remember what it is.\N{\rChinese}但记住它是什么。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.28,1:00:41.66,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Let's take two things that you know very well and merge them together.\N{\rChinese}好了？先拿两件你很熟悉的事，合并在一起。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.88,1:00:43.94,English,,0,0,0,,And then you can experience what the oral tradition is.\N{\rChinese}然后你就能体验口头传统的感觉。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.14,1:00:46.38,English,,0,0,0,,It's basically the immersion of a movie.\N{\rChinese}它基本就是电影般的沉浸感。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.66,1:00:48.04,English,,0,0,0,,Think of going to a good movie.\N{\rChinese}想象你去看一场好电影。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.14,1:00:50.50,English,,0,0,0,,And remember the power,\N{\rChinese}记住那份力量，
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.92,1:00:52.74,English,,0,0,0,,the immersive power of being in that movie.\N{\rChinese}那种沉浸在电影中的力量。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.84,1:00:54.38,English,,0,0,0,,You are in that movie. Okay?\N{\rChinese}你正身处于那部电影之中。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.98,1:00:58.00,English,,0,0,0,,You combine it with the intimacy of a conversation.\N{\rChinese}你把它与对话的亲密感结合起来。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.38,1:01:02.70,English,,0,0,0,,Just think of like having this four or five hour conversation with your best friend\N{\rChinese}想象你和最好的朋友进行四五个小时的对话，聊聊人生和爱情。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.70,1:01:05.38,English,,0,0,0,,and talking about life and love in general.\N{\rChinese}and talking about life and love in general.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.52,1:01:08.56,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The oral tradition combines these two things.\N{\rChinese}好的？口述传统把这两件事结合在一起。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.70,1:01:10.08,English,,0,0,0,,And that's why it's so powerful.\N{\rChinese}这就是它之所以如此强大的原因。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.50,1:01:13.82,English,,0,0,0,,That's why it cannot be remembered.\N{\rChinese}这就是它之所以能被记住的原因。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.72,1:01:18.24,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The Viking oral tradition was extremely powerful.\N{\rChinese}好的？维京口述传统极其强大。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.36,1:01:21.36,English,,0,0,0,,But it was so powerful that it cannot be remembered.\N{\rChinese}但它如此强大，以至可记住。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.26,1:01:26.18,English,,0,0,0,,It cannot be written down. But\N{\rChinese}可写下来。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.18,1:01:27.84,English,,0,0,0,,as I will show you in future classes,\N{\rChinese}正如我在后续课程中会展示的那样，
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.16,1:01:31.92,English,,0,0,0,,this oral tradition will go on to influence\N{\rChinese}这口述传统将继续影响
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.58,1:01:33.96,English,,0,0,0,,major European civilization,\N{\rChinese}欧洲主要文明
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.42,1:01:38.94,English,,0,0,0,,specifically the Germans and the British, but also the Russians as well.\N{\rChinese}具体来说是德国人和英国人，也包括俄罗斯人。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.98,1:01:43.84,English,,0,0,0,,All right. So\N{\rChinese}好的。那么
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.84,1:01:47.34,English,,0,0,0,,again, for most of human history, we as humans have shared our stories\N{\rChinese}再说一次，几乎在人的历史上，我们人类都共享着我们的故事
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.36,1:01:49.00,English,,0,0,0,,and we share our time together telling stories.\N{\rChinese}我们一起分享时间，讲故事。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.64,1:01:54.14,English,,0,0,0,,Why did we lose the oral tradition?\N{\rChinese}我们为什么失去了口述传统？
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.88,1:01:57.92,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Remember this. Why did we lose the oral tradition?\N{\rChinese}好的？记住这点。我们为什么失去了口述传统？
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.24,1:02:01.28,English,,0,0,0,,Well, we transitioned to a literary culture that\N{\rChinese}好吧，我们转向了文学文化，
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.28,1:02:03.40,English,,0,0,0,,emphasized reading and writing.\N{\rChinese}强调阅读和写作。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.84,1:02:05.50,English,,0,0,0,,So in school,\N{\rChinese}于是，在学校里，
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.36,1:02:10.46,English,,0,0,0,,we have you read books, but we don't have you tell stories.\N{\rChinese}我们让你读书，却没有让你讲故事。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.52,1:02:14.92,English,,0,0,0,,We don't tell stories to you. We went from paganism to Christianity.\N{\rChinese}我们没有给你讲故事。我们从多神教转向基督教。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.28,1:02:19.34,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The problem with Christianity is it is extremely uh,\N{\rChinese}好的？基督教的问题在于它极其……
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.52,1:02:23.60,English,,0,0,0,,sanctimonious. It focuses on what is good and evil.\N{\rChinese}虔诚。它聚焦于善与恶。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.26,1:02:27.82,English,,0,0,0,,Whereas pagan culture is like whether it's interesting or not interesting.\N{\rChinese}而多神文化则是关于事物是否有趣。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.94,1:02:29.26,English,,0,0,0,,Whether it's memorable or not memorable.\N{\rChinese}是记忆深刻还是平凡无味。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.60,1:02:33.42,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Live a memorable, interesting, adventurous life.\N{\rChinese}好的？过一个记忆深刻、趣味十足、冒险连连的生活。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.10,1:02:35.98,English,,0,0,0,,And the Christians are like, no, that's not good.\N{\rChinese}基督徒们则说，没错，那不算好。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.12,1:02:39.34,English,,0,0,0,,Because if you do that, you're going to create a lot of evil.\N{\rChinese}因为这样做，你就会制造许多的恶事。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.54,1:02:42.56,English,,0,0,0,,So, live a good life.\N{\rChinese}于是，过好日子。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.12,1:02:44.40,English,,0,0,0,,Avoid committing evil.\N{\rChinese}别犯恶事。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.72,1:02:49.12,English,,0,0,0,,And the last thing is, we went from a egalitarian world\N{\rChinese}最后一件事是，我们从平等的世界走向了…
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.12,1:02:52.00,English,,0,0,0,,where everyone can contribute to the story,\N{\rChinese}在这里人人都能为故事添砖瓦，
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.12,1:02:55.04,English,,0,0,0,,to a hierarchical world where the top, the elite,\N{\rChinese}变成一个层级化的世界，顶层是精英，
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.18,1:02:59.68,English,,0,0,0,,insists on indoctrinating us and controlling how we think.\N{\rChinese}他们坚持灌输我们并掌控我们的思维。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.86,1:03:04.32,English,,0,0,0,,Alright? Okay?\N{\rChinese}好的？
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.52,1:03:05.76,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense to you guys?\N{\rChinese}听得懂吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.88,1:03:09.56,English,,0,0,0,,Any questions so far? So\N{\rChinese}到现在还有问题吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.56,1:03:11.98,English,,0,0,0,,this is why we left the oral tradition and\N{\rChinese}这就是我们离开口头传统的原因
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.98,1:03:14.46,English,,0,0,0,,adopted literary and visual culture.\N{\rChinese}采用文学与视觉文化。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.96,1:03:19.46,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So, to conclude the class,\N{\rChinese}好的。于是，为了结束本课，
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.64,1:03:23.30,English,,0,0,0,,I know this is a lot to take in.\N{\rChinese}我知道这信息量很大。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.38,1:03:25.20,English,,0,0,0,,It's a lot of information. I apologize.\N{\rChinese}这是一大堆信息。抱歉。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.48,1:03:27.96,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But, let me conclude with a story.\N{\rChinese}好的？那我用一个故事来收尾。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.00,1:03:33.12,English,,0,0,0,,So, I have two young boys.\N{\rChinese}于是，我有两个小男孩。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.52,1:03:34.80,English,,0,0,0,,And I sleep with them. Okay?\N{\rChinese}我和他们一起睡觉。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.42,1:03:37.84,English,,0,0,0,,And what I do is, I tell them stories.\N{\rChinese}我做的事是给他们讲故事。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.54,1:03:40.26,English,,0,0,0,,I don't have them do math.\N{\rChinese}我让他们不做数学。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.48,1:03:42.50,English,,0,0,0,,I don't have them read books. But I tell them stories.\N{\rChinese}我让他们不读书。但我给他们讲故事。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.94,1:03:44.74,English,,0,0,0,,Where I make them the characters.\N{\rChinese}我把他们设为角色。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.12,1:03:46.60,English,,0,0,0,,The heroes. The heroes of the story.\N{\rChinese}英雄们。故事里的英雄们。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.74,1:03:50.74,English,,0,0,0,,So I'll tell you one story that I told my youngest son, Mao Mao.\N{\rChinese}于是我给你讲一个我曾经给最小的儿子毛毛讲过的故事。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.88,1:03:53.78,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The story goes like this.\N{\rChinese}好的？故事是这样的。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.38,1:03:57.00,English,,0,0,0,,It is Mao Mao's fourth birthday.\N{\rChinese}毛毛四岁生日到了。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.56,1:03:58.94,English,,0,0,0,,And I tell Mao Mao,\N{\rChinese}于是我对毛毛说，
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.50,1:04:02.58,English,,0,0,0,,on your fourth birthday, something magical happens.\N{\rChinese}在你四岁生日时，发生了一件神奇的事。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.40,1:04:06.44,English,,0,0,0,,You can pray to God, and whatever you wish for,\N{\rChinese}你可以向上帝祈祷，随你所愿。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.72,1:04:08.98,English,,0,0,0,,God will grant you your wish.\N{\rChinese}上帝会满足你的愿望。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.56,1:04:14.22,English,,0,0,0,,So Mao Mao is really excited and he thinks a long time about what he wants.\N{\rChinese}于是毛毛非常兴奋，思考很久想要什么。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.22,1:04:17.90,English,,0,0,0,,On his fourth birthday, he prays to God and says,\N{\rChinese}在他四岁生日时，他向上帝祈祷并说，
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.20,1:04:21.74,English,,0,0,0,,I wish for a room full\N{\rChinese}我想要一个满满的房间
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.74,1:04:24.54,English,,0,0,0,,of strawberries every single day.\N{\rChinese}每天都有草莓。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.26,1:04:28.96,English,,0,0,0,,He says that, and God immediately responds.\N{\rChinese}他说了这句话，上帝立刻回应。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.66,1:04:33.86,English,,0,0,0,,Immediately, in his room, it's full of strawberries.\N{\rChinese}立刻，房间里满满的草莓。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.10,1:04:36.46,English,,0,0,0,,And Mao Mao, he loves strawberries.\N{\rChinese}毛毛，真爱草莓。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.64,1:04:39.86,English,,0,0,0,,He eats it right away. The next day,\N{\rChinese}他立刻吃下去。第二天，房间又满满的草莓。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.14,1:04:43.26,English,,0,0,0,,the room is also full of strawberries.\N{\rChinese}房间又满满的草莓。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.34,1:04:45.90,English,,0,0,0,,And he eats it, and the next day, The third day, again.\N{\rChinese}他吃了，第二天，第三天，又吃了。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.14,1:04:48.74,English,,0,0,0,,But by the fourth day, he's kind of sick of strawberries.\N{\rChinese}到第四天，他有点吃腻草莓。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.64,1:04:53.44,English,,0,0,0,,So eventually, strawberries overflow and fill the house.\N{\rChinese}于是，草莓溢满屋子。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.44,1:04:56.50,English,,0,0,0,,And then they fill the street.\N{\rChinese}随后，草莓洒满街道。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.38,1:04:59.82,English,,0,0,0,,At this time, the neighbors are really worried.\N{\rChinese}此时，邻居们真担心。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.30,1:05:03.10,English,,0,0,0,,And we have to explain to our neighbors, oh, it's because\N{\rChinese}我们得向邻居解释，哦，原因是
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.10,1:05:06.04,English,,0,0,0,,Mao Mao wished for strawberries,\N{\rChinese}毛毛想要草莓，
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.30,1:05:08.08,English,,0,0,0,,and that's why we have so many strawberries.\N{\rChinese}于是我们就有这么多草莓。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.34,1:05:10.60,English,,0,0,0,,But hey, let's share strawberries together.\N{\rChinese}但嘿，让我们一起分享草莓。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.90,1:05:15.00,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And the neighbors are at first happy, but then eventually, they get sick of strawberries too.\N{\rChinese}好的？邻居们起初时很开心，随后又被草莓搞得厌烦。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.32,1:05:17.64,English,,0,0,0,,And then the strawberries fill the entire street.\N{\rChinese}然后草莓洒满整条街道。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.40,1:05:20.96,English,,0,0,0,,Then the city of Beijing is filled with the strawberries.\N{\rChinese}然后北京城里满是草莓。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.80,1:05:23.16,English,,0,0,0,,Now it's a national emergency.\N{\rChinese}现在是全国紧急情况。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.64,1:05:27.76,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The military come, scientists come, and we're ever trying to resolve this issue.\N{\rChinese}军队来了，科学家来了，我们一直在努力解决这个问题。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.14,1:05:30.58,English,,0,0,0,,Then the whole country of China is filled with strawberries.\N{\rChinese}然后整个中国都被草莓覆盖。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.82,1:05:34.90,English,,0,0,0,,Then the whole continent of Asia is filled with strawberries.\N{\rChinese}随后整个亚洲都被草莓覆盖。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.64,1:05:39.12,English,,0,0,0,,Eventually, everyone has to get on a spaceship and get out of,\N{\rChinese}最终，大家都得登上宇宙飞船离开。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.06,1:05:43.80,English,,0,0,0,,get out into space and go to the moon, to recolonize the moon.\N{\rChinese}登上宇宙飞船，飞向月球，重新殖民月球。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.28,1:05:48.56,English,,0,0,0,,But strawberries keep on overflowing until they reach the moon.\N{\rChinese}草莓不断溢出，直至月球。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.60,1:05:53.12,English,,0,0,0,,At this point, the entire world prays,\N{\rChinese}此时，全球皆祈祷。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.12,1:05:57.18,English,,0,0,0,,says to Mao Mao, listen, your fifth birthday is tomorrow.\N{\rChinese}说给毛毛听，五岁生日明天。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.74,1:06:01.06,English,,0,0,0,,Please pray to God and\N{\rChinese}请向上帝祷告，且
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.06,1:06:03.62,English,,0,0,0,,tell him no more strawberries.\N{\rChinese}再告他草莓不再来。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.16,1:06:08.48,English,,0,0,0,,Mao Mao, if you do this for us, we will make you president and king of the world.\N{\rChinese}毛毛，如果你为我们做了这件事，我们会让你成为世界的总统和国王。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.70,1:06:12.02,English,,0,0,0,,We will give you all the chocolate in the world.\N{\rChinese}我们会给你全世界的巧克力。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.06,1:06:13.42,English,,0,0,0,,We'll give you all the gold in the world.\N{\rChinese}我们会给你全世界的黄金。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.50,1:06:18.40,English,,0,0,0,,Can you please do this? Can you please tell God no more strawberries?\N{\rChinese}请你做这件事吧？请你告诉上帝不再送草莓吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.86,1:06:21.10,English,,0,0,0,,If you do that, we'll give you all the chocolate in the world.\N{\rChinese}如果你这么做，我们会给你全世界的巧克力。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.02,1:06:23.96,English,,0,0,0,,Mao Mao says, yes, I will.\N{\rChinese}毛毛说，好的，我会的。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.56,1:06:25.96,English,,0,0,0,,And on his fifth birthday,\N{\rChinese}在他五岁生日那天，
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.36,1:06:28.20,English,,0,0,0,,Mao Mao closes her eyes,\N{\rChinese}毛毛闭上眼睛，
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.14,1:06:31.46,English,,0,0,0,,prays to God and says, dear God,\N{\rChinese}祈祷上帝并说，亲爱的上帝，
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.40,1:06:35.88,English,,0,0,0,,I wish for a room full of chocolate every day.\N{\rChinese}我每天都想有一间满满的巧克力房间。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.18,1:06:38.98,English,,0,0,0,,And that's how the story ends. Okay?\N{\rChinese}于是故事就这样结束了。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.46,1:06:41.96,English,,0,0,0,,Now, it's a very strange story.\N{\rChinese}现在，这个故事很奇怪。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.96,1:06:43.36,English,,0,0,0,,But guess what?\N{\rChinese}但你猜怎么了？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.50,1:06:45.64,English,,0,0,0,,My son's going to remember this for a long time.\N{\rChinese}我儿子会记住这件事很久。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.86,1:06:51.06,English,,0,0,0,,But knowing that, it's going to inspire him to think about the story\N{\rChinese}知道了这件事，他会被激发去思考这段故事。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.06,1:06:52.56,English,,0,0,0,,and tell his own stories.\N{\rChinese}并讲述自己的故事。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.64,1:06:57.90,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? All he has to do is change the story a bit, and now he has his own story.\N{\rChinese}好的？他只需要稍微改动故事，现在他就有自己的故事。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.10,1:07:00.72,English,,0,0,0,,He can change the characters. He can change some of the details.\N{\rChinese}他可以改角色，也可以改细节。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.28,1:07:03.44,English,,0,0,0,,All right? That's the power of the old tradition.\N{\rChinese}好的？这就是古老传统的力量。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.26,1:07:07.36,English,,0,0,0,,But if I were to write down this story,\N{\rChinese}但如果我要把这个故事写下来，
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.98,1:07:09.60,English,,0,0,0,,I couldn't say it in this way.\N{\rChinese}我就不能这样说了。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.28,1:07:11.74,English,,0,0,0,,I couldn't do it. Okay?\N{\rChinese}我做不到。好的吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.96,1:07:14.26,English,,0,0,0,,Let's see how I would change the story if I wrote it down.\N{\rChinese}让我看看如果把它写下来，我会怎么改动故事。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.66,1:07:19.40,English,,0,0,0,,Let's do the same story, but now I write it down rather than say it to Mao Mao himself.\N{\rChinese}同样的故事，但这次我写下来，而不是对毛毛说。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.08,1:07:25.70,English,,0,0,0,,For his fourth birthday, Mao Mao prayed to God for a room full of strawberries every day.\N{\rChinese}为他的四岁生日，毛毛祈求上帝每天给他一间满满的草莓房间。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.48,1:07:27.98,English,,0,0,0,,Immediately, his room filled with strawberries.\N{\rChinese}立刻，他的房间就满了草莓。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.34,1:07:32.12,English,,0,0,0,,He ate them happily. The next morning, his room filled with strawberries.\N{\rChinese}他高兴地吃了草莓。第二天早晨，他的房间又满了草莓。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.28,1:07:35.48,English,,0,0,0,,He ate them. The very next morning, his room filled with strawberries.\N{\rChinese}他吃了它们。第二天早晨，他的房间又满了草莓。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.64,1:07:36.94,English,,0,0,0,,He did not eat them.\N{\rChinese}他没有吃它们。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.00,1:07:38.88,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So I have to make this story shorter,\N{\rChinese}好的吗？所以我得把这个故事写短一点。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.04,1:07:43.04,English,,0,0,0,,more compact. So that's easier to read.\N{\rChinese}更紧凑一点，读起来更容易。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.92,1:07:48.78,English,,0,0,0,,The house filled with strawberries, and the street filled with them,\N{\rChinese}房间里满了草莓，街道也满了草莓，随后是城市，再到国家。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.88,1:07:50.82,English,,0,0,0,,then the city, then the country.\N{\rChinese}then the city, then the country.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.02,1:07:54.60,English,,0,0,0,,On his fifth birthday, Mao Mao prayed to God for no more strawberries.\N{\rChinese}在他五岁生日那天，毛毛向上帝祈求不再有草莓。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.14,1:07:58.58,English,,0,0,0,,His room became clean, and Mao Mao understood the power of words.\N{\rChinese}他的房间变得干净，毛毛也明白了文字的力量。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.14,1:08:01.74,English,,0,0,0,,You understand? Why am I doing this?\N{\rChinese}你明白吗？我为什么要这么做？
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.82,1:08:04.12,English,,0,0,0,,Why has literary culture changed the story?\N{\rChinese}文学文化为什么改变了故事？
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.30,1:08:08.84,English,,0,0,0,,Because now I know that the words leave me,\N{\rChinese}因为现在我知道话语离开我，
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.34,1:08:11.96,English,,0,0,0,,and they leave Mao Mao. They go out into the wider world.\N{\rChinese}它们离开毛毛，飞向更广阔的世界。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.36,1:08:16.12,English,,0,0,0,,And therefore, people will judge my words.\N{\rChinese}于是人们会评判我的话语。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.72,1:08:21.88,English,,0,0,0,,They will think that I'm a bad father or whatever.\N{\rChinese}他们会认为我是个坏父亲或其他。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.02,1:08:26.22,English,,0,0,0,,I'm conscious of that. Okay? So I change in a way that is not so offensive.\N{\rChinese}我对此很在意。好了？于是我以不那么冒犯的方式改变。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.94,1:08:30.52,English,,0,0,0,,So that people can better appreciate this.\N{\rChinese}于是人们能更好地欣赏此事。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.08,1:08:34.82,English,,0,0,0,,You understand? Do you see the difference between oral culture and literary culture?\N{\rChinese}你明白吗？你能看出口头文化与文学文化的差别吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.38,1:08:37.78,English,,0,0,0,,In oral culture, you can be intimate.\N{\rChinese}在口头文化里，你可以亲密相处。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.26,1:08:40.02,English,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you can play.\N{\rChinese}因此，你可以演绎。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.20,1:08:42.84,English,,0,0,0,,You can experiment. You can be curious.\N{\rChinese}你可以实验。你可以好奇。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.04,1:08:45.98,English,,0,0,0,,You can be adventurous. And that's what leads to the imagination.\N{\rChinese}你可以冒险。正是如此，才孕育想象。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.94,1:08:49.88,English,,0,0,0,,But in the literary culture, everyone is watching you.\N{\rChinese}但在文学文化里，大家都在注视着你。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.26,1:08:53.62,English,,0,0,0,,A hundred years from now, people are still watching you.\N{\rChinese}一百年后，人们仍在注视着你。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.96,1:08:56.52,English,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you have a sense of shame.\N{\rChinese}于是，你会有一种羞愧感。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.78,1:08:59.80,English,,0,0,0,,You're very conscious about your effect on people.\N{\rChinese}你很在意自己对人们的影响。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.18,1:09:03.00,English,,0,0,0,,All right? So a metaphor we can use is,\N{\rChinese}好了？所以我们可以用一个比喻。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.08,1:09:06.12,English,,0,0,0,,this transition from oral tradition to literary culture,\N{\rChinese}从口头传统到文学文化的过渡，
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.58,1:09:08.52,English,,0,0,0,,is really like the story of Adam and Eve.\N{\rChinese}就像亚当与夏娃的故事。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.64,1:09:09.97,English,,0,0,0,,Adam and Eve. In theori,\N{\rChinese}亚当与夏娃。在理论里，
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.78,1:09:15.88,English,,0,0,0,,you flavor flavor flavor flavor flavor flavor flavor flavor flavor flavor flavor They understood\N{\rChinese}你调味调味调味调味调味调味调味调味调味调味他们懂了
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.88,1:09:19.30,English,,0,0,0,,that they are naked and\N{\rChinese}那他们赤裸无衣
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.30,1:09:20.74,English,,0,0,0,,therefore they're being watched.\N{\rChinese}于是被人注视
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.76,1:09:23.40,English,,0,0,0,,And because of this,\N{\rChinese}于是因为这个，他们被抛出伊甸园。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.50,1:09:27.64,English,,0,0,0,,they are thrown out of the Garden of Eden.\N{\rChinese}他们被抛出伊甸园。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.78,1:09:30.98,English,,0,0,0,,So I want to leave you with that metaphor.\N{\rChinese}于是我想用这个比喻留给你们。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.22,1:09:36.70,English,,0,0,0,,Oral tradition, we leave it behind and we think that it's a good thing.\N{\rChinese}口头传统，我们把它抛在身后，认为它是件好事。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.24,1:09:40.54,English,,0,0,0,,But we tend to forget the power\N{\rChinese}但我们往往忘记了口头传统的力量
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.54,1:09:43.46,English,,0,0,0,,and beauty of the oral tradition.\N{\rChinese}和美感。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.44,1:09:50.14,English,,0,0,0,,So I leave you with three questions to help us better understand\N{\rChinese}于是我留给你们三个问题，帮助我们更好地理解。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.14,1:09:51.46,English,,0,0,0,,and remember the lecture.\N{\rChinese}记住讲座。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.64,1:09:53.62,English,,0,0,0,,The first question is, what is the imagination?\N{\rChinese}第一个问题是，想象是什么？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.98,1:09:56.60,English,,0,0,0,,What is the memory? Well, in the oral tradition,\N{\rChinese}记忆是什么？好吧，在口头传统中，
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.88,1:09:58.88,English,,0,0,0,,we would think that the imagination is just an extension\N{\rChinese}我们会认为想象只是记忆的延伸。通过让我们的故事易记，我们激发想象。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.26,1:10:03.84,English,,0,0,0,,of the memory. By making our stories memorable, we excite the imagination.\N{\rChinese}因此我们允许创作的过程。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.24,1:10:07.06,English,,0,0,0,,Therefore we allow for the process of creation.\N{\rChinese}Therefore we allow forthe process of creation.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.28,1:10:13.08,English,,0,0,0,,Second question is, could we have Homer, Dante, and Shakespeare without the oral tradition?\N{\rChinese}第二个问题是，若没有口头传统，我们会有荷马、但丁和莎士比吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.20,1:10:15.26,English,,0,0,0,,Yes. And the answer, I think, is no.\N{\rChinese}会的。我的答案是不会。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.66,1:10:18.88,English,,0,0,0,,I think we would not have the greatest poetry\N{\rChinese}我认为我们就不会有最伟大的诗歌。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.88,1:10:22.48,English,,0,0,0,,in human history if it were not for the oral tradition.\N{\rChinese}如果不是口头传统，人类历史会怎样？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.44,1:10:25.62,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, if you think about for the past 50 years,\N{\rChinese}事实上，如果你回想过去五十年，
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.18,1:10:29.62,English,,0,0,0,,what has humanity, even though there's like 8 billion of us,\N{\rChinese}人类已经拥有八十亿人，甚至如此，
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.72,1:10:32.76,English,,0,0,0,,we have more wealth and\N{\rChinese}我们拥有比以往更丰富的财富和技术，究竟创作了什么文学巨作？
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.76,1:10:37.12,English,,0,0,0,,technology than ever before, what literary masterpiece have we created?\N{\rChinese}我知道你们在学校读《多伊莱特俱乐部》，但它很糟。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.80,1:10:41.98,English,,0,0,0,,I know you guys read the Doylet Club in school and it sucks.\N{\rChinese}I know you guys read the Doylet Club in school and it sucks.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.18,1:10:43.86,English,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you right now. It's terrible.\N{\rChinese}我现在就告诉你，真糟。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.06,1:10:46.40,English,,0,0,0,,It's a piece of crap. And\N{\rChinese}它是一坯烂作。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.40,1:10:51.02,English,,0,0,0,,I can't think of a literary masterpiece of the past 50 to 60 years.\N{\rChinese}我想不出过去五六十年间的文学巨作。
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.56,1:10:55.06,English,,0,0,0,,There are some very entertaining books, but\N{\rChinese}有一些非常有趣的书，但……
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.06,1:10:59.56,English,,0,0,0,,not of the stature and power of Homer, Dante, and Shakespeare.\N{\rChinese}不及荷马、但丁与莎士比的宏大与力量。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.16,1:11:02.34,English,,0,0,0,,And the last question I have is,\N{\rChinese}还有我最后一个问题是，
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.44,1:11:06.84,English,,0,0,0,,does civilization make us less creative?\N{\rChinese}文明让我们更少创造吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.46,1:11:13.44,English,,0,0,0,,Does being a civilization make us more creative?\N{\rChinese}成为文明让我们更有创造力吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.44,1:11:16.42,English,,0,0,0,,Are we more ashamed of exploring,\N{\rChinese}我们更自豪于探索吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.74,1:11:19.08,English,,0,0,0,,of being curious, of playing?\N{\rChinese}好奇的事，玩耍的事？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.10,1:11:23.86,English,,0,0,0,,Are we less creative because of civilization?\N{\rChinese}文明让我们更少创造吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.66,1:11:27.00,English,,0,0,0,,All right. Okay.\N{\rChinese}好的。好。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.10,1:11:29.16,English,,0,0,0,,So that's it, guys. Any questions?\N{\rChinese}好了，大家。还有问题吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.12,1:11:41.90,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So next week,\N{\rChinese}好的。下周，
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.94,1:11:44.48,English,,0,0,0,,we will do the 11th edition of the Abyssic Caliphate.\N{\rChinese}我们将进行第十一版的深渊哈里发。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.54,1:11:45.78,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? All right.\N{\rChinese}好的？好了。
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.80,1:11:49.58,English,,0,0,0,,So I will see you guys next Tuesday.\N{\rChinese}那我下周二见你们。
